3605/*
3606 * Return TRUE if the current reginput position matches the Visual area.
3607 */
3608static int reg_match_visual(void)
3609{
3610 pos_T top, bot;
3611 linenr_T lnum;
3612 colnr_T col;
3613 win_T *wp = reg_win == NULL((void*)0) ? curwin : reg_win;
3614 int mode;
3615 colnr_T start, end;
3616 colnr_T start2, end2;
3617 colnr_T cols;
3618
3619 /* Check if the buffer is the current buffer. */
3620 if (reg_buf != curbuf || VIsual.lnum == 0)
3621 return FALSE0;
3622
3623 if (VIsual_active) {
3624 if (lt(VIsual, wp->w_cursor)(((VIsual).lnum != (wp->w_cursor).lnum) ? (VIsual).lnum <
(wp->w_cursor).lnum : (VIsual).col != (wp->w_cursor).col
? (VIsual).col < (wp->w_cursor).col : (VIsual).coladd <
(wp->w_cursor).coladd)) {
3625 top = VIsual;
3626 bot = wp->w_cursor;
3627 } else {
3628 top = wp->w_cursor;
3629 bot = VIsual;
3630 }
3631 mode = VIsual_mode;
3632 } else {
3633 if (lt(curbuf->b_visual.vi_start, curbuf->b_visual.vi_end)(((curbuf->b_visual.vi_start).lnum != (curbuf->b_visual
.vi_end).lnum) ? (curbuf->b_visual.vi_start).lnum < (curbuf
->b_visual.vi_end).lnum : (curbuf->b_visual.vi_start).col
!= (curbuf->b_visual.vi_end).col ? (curbuf->b_visual.vi_start
).col < (curbuf->b_visual.vi_end).col : (curbuf->b_visual
.vi_start).coladd < (curbuf->b_visual.vi_end).coladd)) {
3634 top = curbuf->b_visual.vi_start;
3635 bot = curbuf->b_visual.vi_end;
3636 } else {
3637 top = curbuf->b_visual.vi_end;
3638 bot = curbuf->b_visual.vi_start;
3639 }
3640 mode = curbuf->b_visual.vi_mode;
3641 }
3642 lnum = reglnum + reg_firstlnum;
3643 if (lnum < top.lnum || lnum > bot.lnum)
3644 return FALSE0;
3645
3646 if (mode == 'v') {
3647 col = (colnr_T)(reginput - regline);
3648 if ((lnum == top.lnum && col < top.col)
3649 || (lnum == bot.lnum && col >= bot.col + (*p_sel != 'e')))
3650 return FALSE0;
3651 } else if (mode == Ctrl_V22) {
3652 getvvcol(wp, &top, &start, NULL((void*)0), &end);
3653 getvvcol(wp, &bot, &start2, NULL((void*)0), &end2);
3654 if (start2 < start)
3655 start = start2;
3656 if (end2 > end)
3657 end = end2;
3658 if (top.col == MAXCOL(0x7fffffffL) || bot.col == MAXCOL(0x7fffffffL))
3659 end = MAXCOL(0x7fffffffL);
3660 cols = win_linetabsize(wp, regline, (colnr_T)(reginput - regline));
3661 if (cols < start || cols > end - (*p_sel == 'e'))
3662 return FALSE0;
3663 }
3664 return TRUE1;
3665}
3666
3667#define ADVANCE_REGINPUT()reginput += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(reginput) : 1 mb_ptr_adv(reginput)reginput += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(reginput) : 1
3668
3669/*
3670 * The arguments from BRACE_LIMITS are stored here. They are actually local
3671 * to regmatch(), but they are here to reduce the amount of stack space used
3672 * (it can be called recursively many times).
3673 */
3674static long bl_minval;
3675static long bl_maxval;
3676
3677/*
3678 * regmatch - main matching routine
3679 *
3680 * Conceptually the strategy is simple: Check to see whether the current node
3681 * matches, push an item onto the regstack and loop to see whether the rest
3682 * matches, and then act accordingly. In practice we make some effort to
3683 * avoid using the regstack, in particular by going through "ordinary" nodes
3684 * (that don't need to know whether the rest of the match failed) by a nested
3685 * loop.
3686 *
3687 * Returns TRUE when there is a match. Leaves reginput and reglnum just after
3688 * the last matched character.
3689 * Returns FALSE when there is no match. Leaves reginput and reglnum in an
3690 * undefined state!
3691 */
3692static int
3693regmatch (
3694 char_u *scan /* Current node. */
3695)
3696{
3697 char_u *next; /* Next node. */
3698 int op;
3699 int c;
3700 regitem_T *rp;
3701 int no;
3702 int status; /* one of the RA_ values: */
3703#define RA_FAIL1 1 /* something failed, abort */
3704#define RA_CONT2 2 /* continue in inner loop */
3705#define RA_BREAK3 3 /* break inner loop */
3706#define RA_MATCH4 4 /* successful match */
3707#define RA_NOMATCH5 5 /* didn't match */
3708
3709 /* Make "regstack" and "backpos" empty. They are allocated and freed in
3710 * bt_regexec_both() to reduce malloc()/free() calls. */
3711 regstack.ga_len = 0;
3712 backpos.ga_len = 0;
3713
3714 /*
3715 * Repeat until "regstack" is empty.
3716 */
3717 for (;; ) {
3718 /* Some patterns may take a long time to match, e.g., "\([a-z]\+\)\+Q".
3719 * Allow interrupting them with CTRL-C. */
3720 fast_breakcheck();
3721
3722#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
3723 if (scan != NULL((void*)0) && regnarrate) {
3724 mch_errmsg((char *)regprop(scan))fprintf(stderr, "%s", ((char *)regprop(scan)));
3725 mch_errmsg("(\n")fprintf(stderr, "%s", ("(\n"));
3726 }
3727#endif
3728
3729 /*
3730 * Repeat for items that can be matched sequentially, without using the
3731 * regstack.
3732 */
3733 for (;; ) {
3734 if (got_int || scan == NULL((void*)0)) {
3735 status = RA_FAIL1;
3736 break;
3737 }
3738 status = RA_CONT2;
3739
3740#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
3741 if (regnarrate) {
3742 mch_errmsg((char *)regprop(scan))fprintf(stderr, "%s", ((char *)regprop(scan)));
3743 mch_errmsg("...\n")fprintf(stderr, "%s", ("...\n"));
3744 if (re_extmatch_in != NULL((void*)0)) {
3745 int i;
3746
3747 mch_errmsg(_("External submatches:\n"))fprintf(stderr, "%s", (gettext((char *)("External submatches:\n"
))));
3748 for (i = 0; i < NSUBEXP10; i++) {
3749 mch_errmsg(" \"")fprintf(stderr, "%s", (" \""));
3750 if (re_extmatch_in->matches[i] != NULL((void*)0))
3751 mch_errmsg((char *)re_extmatch_in->matches[i])fprintf(stderr, "%s", ((char *)re_extmatch_in->matches[i])
);
3752 mch_errmsg("\"\n")fprintf(stderr, "%s", ("\"\n"));
3753 }
3754 }
3755 }
3756#endif
3757 next = regnext(scan);
3758
3759 op = OP(scan)((int)*(scan));
3760 /* Check for character class with NL added. */
3761 if (!reg_line_lbr && WITH_NL(op)((op) >= 20 + 30 && (op) <= 48 + 30) && REG_MULTI(reg_match == ((void*)0))
3762 && *reginput == NUL'\000' && reglnum <= reg_maxline) {
3763 reg_nextline();
3764 } else if (reg_line_lbr && WITH_NL(op)((op) >= 20 + 30 && (op) <= 48 + 30) && *reginput == '\n') {
3765 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()reginput += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(reginput) : 1;
3766 } else {
3767 if (WITH_NL(op)((op) >= 20 + 30 && (op) <= 48 + 30))
3768 op -= ADD_NL30;
3769 if (has_mbyte)
3770 c = (*mb_ptr2char)(reginput);
3771 else
3772 c = *reginput;
3773 switch (op) {
3774 case BOL1:
3775 if (reginput != regline)
3776 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3777 break;
3778
3779 case EOL2:
3780 if (c != NUL'\000')
3781 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3782 break;
3783
3784 case RE_BOF201:
3785 /* We're not at the beginning of the file when below the first
3786 * line where we started, not at the start of the line or we
3787 * didn't start at the first line of the buffer. */
3788 if (reglnum != 0 || reginput != regline
3789 || (REG_MULTI(reg_match == ((void*)0)) && reg_firstlnum > 1))
3790 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3791 break;
3792
3793 case RE_EOF202:
3794 if (reglnum != reg_maxline || c != NUL'\000')
3795 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3796 break;
3797
3798 case CURSOR203:
3799 /* Check if the buffer is in a window and compare the
3800 * reg_win->w_cursor position to the match position. */
3801 if (reg_win == NULL((void*)0)
3802 || (reglnum + reg_firstlnum != reg_win->w_cursor.lnum)
3803 || ((colnr_T)(reginput - regline) != reg_win->w_cursor.col))
3804 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3805 break;
3806
3807 case RE_MARK207:
3808 /* Compare the mark position to the match position. */
3809 {
3810 int mark = OPERAND(scan)((scan) + 3)[0];
3811 int cmp = OPERAND(scan)((scan) + 3)[1];
3812 pos_T *pos;
3813
3814 pos = getmark_buf(reg_buf, mark, FALSE0);
3815 if (pos == NULL((void*)0) /* mark doesn't exist */
3816 || pos->lnum <= 0 /* mark isn't set in reg_buf */
3817 || (pos->lnum == reglnum + reg_firstlnum
3818 ? (pos->col == (colnr_T)(reginput - regline)
3819 ? (cmp == '<' || cmp == '>')
3820 : (pos->col < (colnr_T)(reginput - regline)
3821 ? cmp != '>'
3822 : cmp != '<'))
3823 : (pos->lnum < reglnum + reg_firstlnum
3824 ? cmp != '>'
3825 : cmp != '<')))
3826 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3827 }
3828 break;
3829
3830 case RE_VISUAL208:
3831 if (!reg_match_visual())
3832 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3833 break;
3834
3835 case RE_LNUM204:
3836 if (!REG_MULTI(reg_match == ((void*)0)) || !re_num_cmp((long_u)(reglnum + reg_firstlnum),
3837 scan))
3838 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3839 break;
3840
3841 case RE_COL205:
3842 if (!re_num_cmp((long_u)(reginput - regline) + 1, scan))
3843 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3844 break;
3845
3846 case RE_VCOL206:
3847 if (!re_num_cmp((long_u)win_linetabsize(
3848 reg_win == NULL((void*)0) ? curwin : reg_win,
3849 regline, (colnr_T)(reginput - regline)) + 1, scan))
3850 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3851 break;
3852
3853 case BOW15: /* \<word; reginput points to w */
3854 if (c == NUL'\000') /* Can't match at end of line */
3855 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3856 else if (has_mbyte) {
3857 int this_class;
3858
3859 /* Get class of current and previous char (if it exists). */
3860 this_class = mb_get_class_buf(reginput, reg_buf);
3861 if (this_class <= 1)
3862 status = RA_NOMATCH5; /* not on a word at all */
3863 else if (reg_prev_class() == this_class)
3864 status = RA_NOMATCH5; /* previous char is in same word */
3865 } else {
3866 if (!vim_iswordc_buf(c, reg_buf) || (reginput > regline
3867 && vim_iswordc_buf(reginput[-1
3868 ], reg_buf)))
3869 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3870 }
3871 break;
3872
3873 case EOW16: /* word\>; reginput points after d */
3874 if (reginput == regline) /* Can't match at start of line */
3875 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3876 else if (has_mbyte) {
3877 int this_class, prev_class;
3878
3879 /* Get class of current and previous char (if it exists). */
3880 this_class = mb_get_class_buf(reginput, reg_buf);
3881 prev_class = reg_prev_class();
3882 if (this_class == prev_class
3883 || prev_class == 0 || prev_class == 1)
3884 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3885 } else {
3886 if (!vim_iswordc_buf(reginput[-1], reg_buf)
3887 || (reginput[0] != NUL'\000' && vim_iswordc_buf(c, reg_buf)))
3888 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3889 }
3890 break; /* Matched with EOW */
3891
3892 case ANY20:
3893 /* ANY does not match new lines. */
3894 if (c == NUL'\000')
3895 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3896 else
3897 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()reginput += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(reginput) : 1;
3898 break;
3899
3900 case IDENT23:
3901 if (!vim_isIDc(c))
3902 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3903 else
3904 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()reginput += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(reginput) : 1;
3905 break;
3906
3907 case SIDENT24:
3908 if (VIM_ISDIGIT(*reginput)((unsigned)(*reginput) - '0' < 10) || !vim_isIDc(c))
3909 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3910 else
3911 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()reginput += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(reginput) : 1;
3912 break;
3913
3914 case KWORD25:
3915 if (!vim_iswordp_buf(reginput, reg_buf))
3916 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3917 else
3918 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()reginput += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(reginput) : 1;
3919 break;
3920
3921 case SKWORD26:
3922 if (VIM_ISDIGIT(*reginput)((unsigned)(*reginput) - '0' < 10) || !vim_iswordp_buf(reginput, reg_buf))
3923 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3924 else
3925 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()reginput += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(reginput) : 1;
3926 break;
3927
3928 case FNAME27:
3929 if (!vim_isfilec(c))
3930 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3931 else
3932 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()reginput += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(reginput) : 1;
3933 break;
3934
3935 case SFNAME28:
3936 if (VIM_ISDIGIT(*reginput)((unsigned)(*reginput) - '0' < 10) || !vim_isfilec(c))
3937 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3938 else
3939 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()reginput += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(reginput) : 1;
3940 break;
3941
3942 case PRINT29:
3943 if (!vim_isprintc(PTR2CHAR(reginput)(has_mbyte ? mb_ptr2char(reginput) : (int)*(reginput))))
3944 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3945 else
3946 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()reginput += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(reginput) : 1;
3947 break;
3948
3949 case SPRINT30:
3950 if (VIM_ISDIGIT(*reginput)((unsigned)(*reginput) - '0' < 10) || !vim_isprintc(PTR2CHAR(reginput)(has_mbyte ? mb_ptr2char(reginput) : (int)*(reginput))))
3951 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3952 else
3953 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()reginput += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(reginput) : 1;
3954 break;
3955
3956 case WHITE31:
3957 if (!vim_iswhite(c)((c) == ' ' || (c) == '\t'))
3958 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3959 else
3960 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()reginput += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(reginput) : 1;
3961 break;
3962
3963 case NWHITE32:
3964 if (c == NUL'\000' || vim_iswhite(c)((c) == ' ' || (c) == '\t'))
3965 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3966 else
3967 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()reginput += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(reginput) : 1;
3968 break;
3969
3970 case DIGIT33:
3971 if (!ri_digit(c)(c < 0x100 && (class_tab[c] & 0x01)))
3972 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3973 else
3974 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()reginput += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(reginput) : 1;
3975 break;
3976
3977 case NDIGIT34:
3978 if (c == NUL'\000' || ri_digit(c)(c < 0x100 && (class_tab[c] & 0x01)))
3979 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3980 else
3981 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()reginput += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(reginput) : 1;
3982 break;
3983
3984 case HEX35:
3985 if (!ri_hex(c)(c < 0x100 && (class_tab[c] & 0x02)))
3986 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3987 else
3988 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()reginput += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(reginput) : 1;
3989 break;
3990
3991 case NHEX36:
3992 if (c == NUL'\000' || ri_hex(c)(c < 0x100 && (class_tab[c] & 0x02)))
3993 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
3994 else
3995 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()reginput += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(reginput) : 1;
3996 break;
3997
3998 case OCTAL37:
3999 if (!ri_octal(c)(c < 0x100 && (class_tab[c] & 0x04)))
4000 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
4001 else

4003 break;
4004

4024 break;

4031 break;
4032

4034 if (c == NUL'\000' || ri_head(c)(c < 0x100 && (class_tab[c] & 0x10)))
4035 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
4036 else

4038 break;
4039
4040 case ALPHA43:
4041 if (!ri_alpha(c)(c < 0x100 && (class_tab[c] & 0x20)))
4042 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
4043 else
4044 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()reginput += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(reginput) : 1;
4045 break;
4046

4048 if (c == NUL'\000' || ri_alpha(c)(c < 0x100 && (class_tab[c] & 0x20)))
4049 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
4050 else

4052 break;
4053
4054 case LOWER45:
4055 if (!ri_lower(c)(c < 0x100 && (class_tab[c] & 0x40)))
4056 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
4057 else
4058 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()reginput += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(reginput) : 1;
4059 break;
4060
4061 case NLOWER46:
4062 if (c == NUL'\000' || ri_lower(c)(c < 0x100 && (class_tab[c] & 0x40)))
4063 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
4064 else
4065 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()reginput += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(reginput) : 1;
4066 break;
4067
4068 case UPPER47:
4069 if (!ri_upper(c)(c < 0x100 && (class_tab[c] & 0x80)))
4070 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
4071 else
4072 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()reginput += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(reginput) : 1;
4073 break;
4074
4075 case NUPPER48:
4076 if (c == NUL'\000' || ri_upper(c)(c < 0x100 && (class_tab[c] & 0x80)))
4077 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
4078 else
4079 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()reginput += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(reginput) : 1;
4080 break;
4081
4082 case EXACTLY5:
4083 {
4084 int len;
4085 char_u *opnd;
4086
4087 opnd = OPERAND(scan)((scan) + 3);
4088 /* Inline the first byte, for speed. */
4089 if (*opnd != *reginput
4090 && (!ireg_ic || (
4091 !enc_utf8 &&
4092 vim_tolower(*opnd) != vim_tolower(*reginput))))
4093 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
4094 else if (*opnd == NUL'\000') {
4095 /* match empty string always works; happens when "~" is
4096 * empty. */
4097 } else {
4098 if (opnd[1] == NUL'\000' && !(enc_utf8 && ireg_ic)) {
4099 len = 1; /* matched a single byte above */
4100 } else {
4101 // Need to match first byte again for multi-byte.
4102 len = (int)STRLEN(opnd)strlen((char *)(opnd));
4103 if (cstrncmp(opnd, reginput, &len) != 0) {
4104 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
4105 }
4106 }
4107 // Check for following composing character, unless %C
4108 // follows (skips over all composing chars).
4109 if (status != RA_NOMATCH5 && enc_utf8
4110 && UTF_COMPOSINGLIKE(reginput, reginput + len)utf_composinglike((reginput), (reginput + len))
4111 && !ireg_icombine
4112 && OP(next)((int)*(next)) != RE_COMPOSING209) {
4113 // raaron: This code makes a composing character get
4114 // ignored, which is the correct behavior (sometimes)
4115 // for voweled Hebrew texts.
4116 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
4117 }
4118 if (status != RA_NOMATCH5) {
4119 reginput += len;
4120 }
4121 }
4122 }
4123 break;
4124
4125 case ANYOF21:
4126 case ANYBUT22:
4127 if (c == NUL'\000')
4128 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
4129 else if ((cstrchr(OPERAND(scan)((scan) + 3), c) == NULL((void*)0)) == (op == ANYOF21))
4130 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
4131 else
4132 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()reginput += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(reginput) : 1;
4133 break;
4134
4135 case MULTIBYTECODE200:
4136 if (has_mbyte) {
4137 int i, len;
4138 char_u *opnd;
4139 int opndc = 0, inpc;
4140
4141 opnd = OPERAND(scan)((scan) + 3);
4142 /* Safety check (just in case 'encoding' was changed since
4143 * compiling the program). */
4144 if ((len = (*mb_ptr2len)(opnd)) < 2) {
4145 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
4146 break;
4147 }
4148 if (enc_utf8)
4149 opndc = mb_ptr2char(opnd);
4150 if (enc_utf8 && utf_iscomposing(opndc)) {
4151 /* When only a composing char is given match at any
4152 * position where that composing char appears. */
4153 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
4154 for (i = 0; reginput[i] != NUL'\000'; i += utf_char2len(inpc)) {
4155 inpc = mb_ptr2char(reginput + i);
4156 if (!utf_iscomposing(inpc)) {
4157 if (i > 0)
4158 break;
4159 } else if (opndc == inpc) {
4160 /* Include all following composing chars. */
4161 len = i + mb_ptr2len(reginput + i);
4162 status = RA_MATCH4;
4163 break;
4164 }
4165 }
4166 } else
4167 for (i = 0; i < len; ++i)
4168 if (opnd[i] != reginput[i]) {
4169 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
4170 break;
4171 }
4172 reginput += len;
4173 } else
4174 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
4175 break;
4176
4177 case RE_COMPOSING209:
4178 if (enc_utf8) {
4179 // Skip composing characters.
4180 while (utf_iscomposing(utf_ptr2char(reginput))) {
4181 mb_cptr_adv(reginput)reginput += enc_utf8 ? utf_ptr2len(reginput) : has_mbyte ? (*
mb_ptr2len)(reginput) : 1;
4182 }
4183 }
4184 break;
4185
4186 case NOTHING6:
4187 break;
4188
4189 case BACK4:
4190 {
4191 int i;
4192
4193 /*
4194 * When we run into BACK we need to check if we don't keep
4195 * looping without matching any input. The second and later
4196 * times a BACK is encountered it fails if the input is still
4197 * at the same position as the previous time.
4198 * The positions are stored in "backpos" and found by the
4199 * current value of "scan", the position in the RE program.
4200 */
4201 backpos_T *bp = (backpos_T *)backpos.ga_data;
4202 for (i = 0; i < backpos.ga_len; ++i)
4203 if (bp[i].bp_scan == scan)
4204 break;
4205 if (i == backpos.ga_len) {
4206 backpos_T *p = GA_APPEND_VIA_PTR(backpos_T, &backpos)ga_append_via_ptr(&backpos, sizeof(backpos_T));
4207 p->bp_scan = scan;
4208 } else if (reg_save_equal(&bp[i].bp_pos))
4209 /* Still at same position as last time, fail. */
4210 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
4211
4212 if (status != RA_FAIL1 && status != RA_NOMATCH5)
4213 reg_save(&bp[i].bp_pos, &backpos);
4214 }
4215 break;
4216
4217 case MOPEN80 + 0: /* Match start: \zs */
4218 case MOPEN80 + 1: /* \( */
4219 case MOPEN80 + 2:
4220 case MOPEN80 + 3:
4221 case MOPEN80 + 4:
4222 case MOPEN80 + 5:
4223 case MOPEN80 + 6:
4224 case MOPEN80 + 7:
4225 case MOPEN80 + 8:
4226 case MOPEN80 + 9:
4227 {
4228 no = op - MOPEN80;
4229 cleanup_subexpr();
4230 rp = regstack_push(RS_MOPEN, scan);
4231 if (rp == NULL((void*)0))
4232 status = RA_FAIL1;
4233 else {
4234 rp->rs_no = no;
4235 save_se(&rp->rs_un.sesave, &reg_startpos[no],(reg_match == ((void*)0)) ? save_se_multi((&rp->rs_un.
sesave), (&reg_startpos[no])) : save_se_one((&rp->

4341 * line. */

) + ((long)(scan)[5] << 8) + (long)(scan)[6]);

<< 16) + ((long)((scan) + 4)[5] << 8) + (long)((
scan) + 4)[6]);

4438
4439 case BRACE_COMPLEX140 + 0:
4440 case BRACE_COMPLEX140 + 1:
4441 case BRACE_COMPLEX140 + 2:
4442 case BRACE_COMPLEX140 + 3:
4443 case BRACE_COMPLEX140 + 4:
4444 case BRACE_COMPLEX140 + 5:
4445 case BRACE_COMPLEX140 + 6:
4446 case BRACE_COMPLEX140 + 7:
4447 case BRACE_COMPLEX140 + 8:
4448 case BRACE_COMPLEX140 + 9:
4449 {
4450 no = op - BRACE_COMPLEX140;
4451 ++brace_count[no];
4452
4453 /* If not matched enough times yet, try one more */
4454 if (brace_count[no] <= (brace_min[no] <= brace_max[no]
4455 ? brace_min[no] : brace_max[no])) {
4456 rp = regstack_push(RS_BRCPLX_MORE, scan);
4457 if (rp == NULL((void*)0))
4458 status = RA_FAIL1;
4459 else {
4460 rp->rs_no = no;
4461 reg_save(&rp->rs_un.regsave, &backpos);
4462 next = OPERAND(scan)((scan) + 3);
4463 /* We continue and handle the result when done. */

4469 if (brace_min[no] <= brace_max[no]) {

4471 if (brace_count[no] <= brace_max[no]) {
4472 rp = regstack_push(RS_BRCPLX_LONG, scan);
4473 if (rp == NULL((void*)0))
4474 status = RA_FAIL1;

4476 rp->rs_no = no;
4477 reg_save(&rp->rs_un.regsave, &backpos);
4478 next = OPERAND(scan)((scan) + 3);
4479 /* We continue and handle the result when done. */
4480 }
4481 }
4482 } else {
4483 /* Range is backwards, use shortest match first */
4484 if (brace_count[no] <= brace_min[no]) {
4485 rp = regstack_push(RS_BRCPLX_SHORT, scan);
4486 if (rp == NULL((void*)0))
4487 status = RA_FAIL1;
4488 else {
4489 reg_save(&rp->rs_un.regsave, &backpos);
4490 /* We continue and handle the result when done. */
4491 }
4492 }

4497 case BRACE_SIMPLE14:
4498 case STAR7:
4499 case PLUS8:
4500 {
4501 regstar_T rst;
4502
4503 /*
4504 * Lookahead to avoid useless match attempts when we know
4505 * what character comes next.
4506 */
4507 if (OP(next)((int)*(next)) == EXACTLY5) {
4508 rst.nextb = *OPERAND(next)((next) + 3);
4509 if (ireg_ic) {
4510 if (vim_isupper(rst.nextb))
4511 rst.nextb_ic = vim_tolower(rst.nextb);
4512 else
4513 rst.nextb_ic = vim_toupper(rst.nextb);
4514 } else
4515 rst.nextb_ic = rst.nextb;
4516 } else {
4517 rst.nextb = NUL'\000';
4518 rst.nextb_ic = NUL'\000';

4521 rst.minval = (op == STAR7) ? 0 : 1;
4522 rst.maxval = MAX_LIMIT(32767L << 16L);

4524 rst.minval = bl_minval;
4525 rst.maxval = bl_maxval;

4529 * When maxval > minval, try matching as much as possible, up
4530 * to maxval. When maxval < minval, try matching at least the
4531 * minimal number (since the range is backwards, that's also
4532 * maxval!).

4535 if (got_int) {
4536 status = RA_FAIL1;
4537 break;
4538 }
4539 if (rst.minval <= rst.maxval
4540 ? rst.count >= rst.minval : rst.count >= rst.maxval) {

4542 * follows. The code is below. Parameters are stored in

4545 EMSG(_(e_maxmempat))emsg((char_u *)(gettext((char *)(e_maxmempat))));
4546 status = RA_FAIL1;

4548 ga_grow(&regstack, sizeof(regstar_T));
4549 regstack.ga_len += sizeof(regstar_T);
4550 rp = regstack_push(rst.minval <= rst.maxval
4551 ? RS_STAR_LONG : RS_STAR_SHORT, scan);
4552 if (rp == NULL((void*)0))
4553 status = RA_FAIL1;
4554 else {
4555 *(((regstar_T *)rp) - 1) = rst;
4556 status = RA_BREAK3; /* skip the restore bits */
4557 }
4558 }
4559 } else
4560 status = RA_NOMATCH5;

4564
4565 case NOMATCH10:
4566 case MATCH9:
4567 case SUBPAT13:

4573 reg_save(&rp->rs_un.regsave, &backpos);

4576 }

4578
4579 case BEHIND11:
4580 case NOBEHIND12:

4582 if ((long)((unsigned)regstack.ga_len >> 10) >= p_mmp) {
4583 EMSG(_(e_maxmempat))emsg((char_u *)(gettext((char *)(e_maxmempat))));
4584 status = RA_FAIL1;

4599 * check the behind match by looping. */
4600 }

4602 break;
4603
4604 case BHPOS19:
4605 if (REG_MULTI(reg_match == ((void*)0))) {

4607 || behind_pos.rs_u.pos.lnum != reglnum)
4608 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
4609 } else if (behind_pos.rs_u.ptr != reginput)
4610 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
4611 break;
4612
4613 case NEWL18:
4614 if ((c != NUL'\000' || !REG_MULTI(reg_match == ((void*)0)) || reglnum > reg_maxline
4615 || reg_line_lbr) && (c != '\n' || !reg_line_lbr))

4617 else if (reg_line_lbr)

4622
4623 case END0:
4624 status = RA_MATCH4; /* Success! */

4626
4627 default:

4629#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
4630 printf("Illegal op code %d\n", op);
4631#endif
4632 status = RA_FAIL1;
4633 break;
4634 }
4635 }
4636
4637 /* If we can't continue sequentially, break the inner loop. */
4638 if (status != RA_CONT2)
4639 break;
4640
4641 /* Continue in inner loop, advance to next item. */
4642 scan = next;
4643
4644 } /* end of inner loop */
4645
4646 /*
4647 * If there is something on the regstack execute the code for the state.
4648 * If the state is popped then loop and use the older state.
4649 */
4650 while (!GA_EMPTY(&regstack)((&regstack)->ga_len <= 0) && status != RA_FAIL1) {
4651 rp = (regitem_T *)((char *)regstack.ga_data + regstack.ga_len) - 1;
4652 switch (rp->rs_state) {
4653 case RS_NOPEN:
4654 /* Result is passed on as-is, simply pop the state. */
4655 regstack_pop(&scan);
4656 break;
4657
4658 case RS_MOPEN:
4659 /* Pop the state. Restore pointers when there is no match. */
4660 if (status == RA_NOMATCH5)
4661 restore_se(&rp->rs_un.sesave, &reg_startpos[rp->rs_no],{ if ((reg_match == ((void*)0))) *(&reg_startpos[rp->rs_no
]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave)->se_u.pos; else *(&reg_startp
[rp->rs_no]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave)->se_u.ptr; }
4662 &reg_startp[rp->rs_no]){ if ((reg_match == ((void*)0))) *(&reg_startpos[rp->rs_no
]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave)->se_u.pos; else *(&reg_startp
[rp->rs_no]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave)->se_u.ptr; };
4663 regstack_pop(&scan);
4664 break;
4665
4666 case RS_ZOPEN:
4667 /* Pop the state. Restore pointers when there is no match. */
4668 if (status == RA_NOMATCH5)
4669 restore_se(&rp->rs_un.sesave, &reg_startzpos[rp->rs_no],{ if ((reg_match == ((void*)0))) *(&reg_startzpos[rp->
rs_no]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave)->se_u.pos; else *(&
reg_startzp[rp->rs_no]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave)->se_u
.ptr; }
4670 &reg_startzp[rp->rs_no]){ if ((reg_match == ((void*)0))) *(&reg_startzpos[rp->
rs_no]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave)->se_u.pos; else *(&
reg_startzp[rp->rs_no]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave)->se_u
.ptr; };
4671 regstack_pop(&scan);
4672 break;
4673
4674 case RS_MCLOSE:
4675 /* Pop the state. Restore pointers when there is no match. */
4676 if (status == RA_NOMATCH5)
4677 restore_se(&rp->rs_un.sesave, &reg_endpos[rp->rs_no],{ if ((reg_match == ((void*)0))) *(&reg_endpos[rp->rs_no
]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave)->se_u.pos; else *(&reg_endp
[rp->rs_no]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave)->se_u.ptr; }
4678 &reg_endp[rp->rs_no]){ if ((reg_match == ((void*)0))) *(&reg_endpos[rp->rs_no
]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave)->se_u.pos; else *(&reg_endp
[rp->rs_no]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave)->se_u.ptr; };
4679 regstack_pop(&scan);
4680 break;
4681
4682 case RS_ZCLOSE:
4683 /* Pop the state. Restore pointers when there is no match. */
4684 if (status == RA_NOMATCH5)
4685 restore_se(&rp->rs_un.sesave, &reg_endzpos[rp->rs_no],{ if ((reg_match == ((void*)0))) *(&reg_endzpos[rp->rs_no
]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave)->se_u.pos; else *(&reg_endzp
[rp->rs_no]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave)->se_u.ptr; }
4686 &reg_endzp[rp->rs_no]){ if ((reg_match == ((void*)0))) *(&reg_endzpos[rp->rs_no
]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave)->se_u.pos; else *(&reg_endzp
[rp->rs_no]) = (&rp->rs_un.sesave)->se_u.ptr; };
4687 regstack_pop(&scan);
4688 break;
4689
4690 case RS_BRANCH:
4691 if (status == RA_MATCH4)
4692 /* this branch matched, use it */
4693 regstack_pop(&scan);
4694 else {
4695 if (status != RA_BREAK3) {
4696 /* After a non-matching branch: try next one. */
4697 reg_restore(&rp->rs_un.regsave, &backpos);
4698 scan = rp->rs_scan;
4699 }
4700 if (scan == NULL((void*)0) || OP(scan)((int)*(scan)) != BRANCH3) {
4701 /* no more branches, didn't find a match */
4702 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
4703 regstack_pop(&scan);
4704 } else {
4705 /* Prepare to try a branch. */
4706 rp->rs_scan = regnext(scan);
4707 reg_save(&rp->rs_un.regsave, &backpos);
4708 scan = OPERAND(scan)((scan) + 3);
4709 }
4710 }
4711 break;
4712
4713 case RS_BRCPLX_MORE:
4714 /* Pop the state. Restore pointers when there is no match. */
4715 if (status == RA_NOMATCH5) {
4716 reg_restore(&rp->rs_un.regsave, &backpos);
4717 --brace_count[rp->rs_no]; /* decrement match count */
4718 }
4719 regstack_pop(&scan);
4720 break;
4721
4722 case RS_BRCPLX_LONG:
4723 /* Pop the state. Restore pointers when there is no match. */
4724 if (status == RA_NOMATCH5) {
4725 /* There was no match, but we did find enough matches. */
4726 reg_restore(&rp->rs_un.regsave, &backpos);
4727 --brace_count[rp->rs_no];
4728 /* continue with the items after "\{}" */
4729 status = RA_CONT2;
4730 }
4731 regstack_pop(&scan);
4732 if (status == RA_CONT2)
4733 scan = regnext(scan);
4734 break;
4735
4736 case RS_BRCPLX_SHORT:
4737 /* Pop the state. Restore pointers when there is no match. */
4738 if (status == RA_NOMATCH5)
4739 /* There was no match, try to match one more item. */
4740 reg_restore(&rp->rs_un.regsave, &backpos);
4741 regstack_pop(&scan);
4742 if (status == RA_NOMATCH5) {
4743 scan = OPERAND(scan)((scan) + 3);
4744 status = RA_CONT2;
4745 }
4746 break;
4747
4748 case RS_NOMATCH:
4749 /* Pop the state. If the operand matches for NOMATCH or
4750 * doesn't match for MATCH/SUBPAT, we fail. Otherwise backup,
4751 * except for SUBPAT, and continue with the next item. */
4752 if (status == (rp->rs_no == NOMATCH10 ? RA_MATCH4 : RA_NOMATCH5))
4753 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
4754 else {
4755 status = RA_CONT2;
4756 if (rp->rs_no != SUBPAT13) /* zero-width */
4757 reg_restore(&rp->rs_un.regsave, &backpos);
4758 }
4759 regstack_pop(&scan);
4760 if (status == RA_CONT2)
4761 scan = regnext(scan);
4762 break;
4763
4764 case RS_BEHIND1:
4765 if (status == RA_NOMATCH5) {
4766 regstack_pop(&scan);
4767 regstack.ga_len -= sizeof(regbehind_T);
4768 } else {
4769 /* The stuff after BEHIND/NOBEHIND matches. Now try if
4770 * the behind part does (not) match before the current
4771 * position in the input. This must be done at every
4772 * position in the input and checking if the match ends at
4773 * the current position. */
4774
4775 /* save the position after the found match for next */
4776 reg_save(&(((regbehind_T *)rp) - 1)->save_after, &backpos);
4777
4778 /* Start looking for a match with operand at the current
4779 * position. Go back one character until we find the
4780 * result, hitting the start of the line or the previous
4781 * line (for multi-line matching).
4782 * Set behind_pos to where the match should end, BHPOS
4783 * will match it. Save the current value. */
4784 (((regbehind_T *)rp) - 1)->save_behind = behind_pos;
4785 behind_pos = rp->rs_un.regsave;
4786
4787 rp->rs_state = RS_BEHIND2;
4788
4789 reg_restore(&rp->rs_un.regsave, &backpos);
4790 scan = OPERAND(rp->rs_scan)((rp->rs_scan) + 3) + 4;
4791 }
4792 break;
4793
4794 case RS_BEHIND2:
4795 /*
4796 * Looping for BEHIND / NOBEHIND match.
4797 */
4798 if (status == RA_MATCH4 && reg_save_equal(&behind_pos)) {
4799 /* found a match that ends where "next" started */
4800 behind_pos = (((regbehind_T *)rp) - 1)->save_behind;
4801 if (rp->rs_no == BEHIND11)
4802 reg_restore(&(((regbehind_T *)rp) - 1)->save_after,
4803 &backpos);
4804 else {
4805 /* But we didn't want a match. Need to restore the
4806 * subexpr, because what follows matched, so they have
4807 * been set. */
4808 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
4809 restore_subexpr(((regbehind_T *)rp) - 1);
4810 }
4811 regstack_pop(&scan);
4812 regstack.ga_len -= sizeof(regbehind_T);
4813 } else {
4814 long limit;
4815
4816 /* No match or a match that doesn't end where we want it: Go
4817 * back one character. May go to previous line once. */
4818 no = OK1;
4819 limit = OPERAND_MIN(rp->rs_scan)(((long)(rp->rs_scan)[3] << 24) + ((long)(rp->rs_scan
)[4] << 16) + ((long)(rp->rs_scan)[5] << 8) + (
long)(rp->rs_scan)[6]);
4820 if (REG_MULTI(reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
4821 if (limit > 0
4822 && ((rp->rs_un.regsave.rs_u.pos.lnum
4823 < behind_pos.rs_u.pos.lnum
4824 ? (colnr_T)STRLEN(regline)strlen((char *)(regline))
4825 : behind_pos.rs_u.pos.col)
4826 - rp->rs_un.regsave.rs_u.pos.col >= limit))
4827 no = FAIL0;
4828 else if (rp->rs_un.regsave.rs_u.pos.col == 0) {
4829 if (rp->rs_un.regsave.rs_u.pos.lnum
4830 < behind_pos.rs_u.pos.lnum
4831 || reg_getline(
4832 --rp->rs_un.regsave.rs_u.pos.lnum)
4833 == NULL((void*)0))
4834 no = FAIL0;
4835 else {
4836 reg_restore(&rp->rs_un.regsave, &backpos);
4837 rp->rs_un.regsave.rs_u.pos.col =
4838 (colnr_T)STRLEN(regline)strlen((char *)(regline));
4839 }
4840 } else {
4841 if (has_mbyte)
4842 rp->rs_un.regsave.rs_u.pos.col -=
4843 (*mb_head_off)(regline, regline
4844 + rp->rs_un.regsave.rs_u.pos.col - 1) + 1;
4845 else
4846 --rp->rs_un.regsave.rs_u.pos.col;
4847 }
4848 } else {
4849 if (rp->rs_un.regsave.rs_u.ptr == regline)
4850 no = FAIL0;
4851 else {
4852 mb_ptr_back(regline, rp->rs_un.regsave.rs_u.ptr)rp->rs_un.regsave.rs_u.ptr -= has_mbyte ? ((*mb_head_off)(
regline, rp->rs_un.regsave.rs_u.ptr - 1) + 1) : 1;
4853 if (limit > 0 && (long)(behind_pos.rs_u.ptr
4854 - rp->rs_un.regsave.rs_u.ptr) > limit)
4855 no = FAIL0;
4856 }
4857 }
4858 if (no == OK1) {
4859 /* Advanced, prepare for finding match again. */
4860 reg_restore(&rp->rs_un.regsave, &backpos);
4861 scan = OPERAND(rp->rs_scan)((rp->rs_scan) + 3) + 4;
4862 if (status == RA_MATCH4) {
4863 /* We did match, so subexpr may have been changed,
4864 * need to restore them for the next try. */
4865 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
4866 restore_subexpr(((regbehind_T *)rp) - 1);
4867 }
4868 } else {
4869 /* Can't advance. For NOBEHIND that's a match. */
4870 behind_pos = (((regbehind_T *)rp) - 1)->save_behind;
4871 if (rp->rs_no == NOBEHIND12) {
4872 reg_restore(&(((regbehind_T *)rp) - 1)->save_after,
4873 &backpos);
4874 status = RA_MATCH4;
4875 } else {
4876 /* We do want a proper match. Need to restore the
4877 * subexpr if we had a match, because they may have
4878 * been set. */
4879 if (status == RA_MATCH4) {
4880 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
4881 restore_subexpr(((regbehind_T *)rp) - 1);
4882 }
4883 }
4884 regstack_pop(&scan);
4885 regstack.ga_len -= sizeof(regbehind_T);
4886 }
4887 }
4888 break;
4889
4890 case RS_STAR_LONG:
4891 case RS_STAR_SHORT:
4892 {
4893 regstar_T *rst = ((regstar_T *)rp) - 1;
4894
4895 if (status == RA_MATCH4) {
4896 regstack_pop(&scan);
4897 regstack.ga_len -= sizeof(regstar_T);
4898 break;
4899 }
4900
4901 /* Tried once already, restore input pointers. */
4902 if (status != RA_BREAK3)
4903 reg_restore(&rp->rs_un.regsave, &backpos);
4904
4905 /* Repeat until we found a position where it could match. */
4906 for (;; ) {
4907 if (status != RA_BREAK3) {
4908 /* Tried first position already, advance. */
4909 if (rp->rs_state == RS_STAR_LONG) {
4910 /* Trying for longest match, but couldn't or
4911 * didn't match -- back up one char. */
4912 if (--rst->count < rst->minval)
4913 break;
4914 if (reginput == regline) {
4915 /* backup to last char of previous line */
4916 --reglnum;
4917 regline = reg_getline(reglnum);
4918 /* Just in case regrepeat() didn't count
4919 * right. */
4920 if (regline == NULL((void*)0))
4921 break;
4922 reginput = regline + STRLEN(regline)strlen((char *)(regline));
4923 fast_breakcheck();
4924 } else
4925 mb_ptr_back(regline, reginput)reginput -= has_mbyte ? ((*mb_head_off)(regline, reginput - 1
) + 1) : 1;
4926 } else {
4927 /* Range is backwards, use shortest match first.
4928 * Careful: maxval and minval are exchanged!
4929 * Couldn't or didn't match: try advancing one
4930 * char. */
4931 if (rst->count == rst->minval
4932 || regrepeat(OPERAND(rp->rs_scan)((rp->rs_scan) + 3), 1L) == 0)
4933 break;
4934 ++rst->count;
4935 }
4936 if (got_int)
4937 break;
4938 } else
4939 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
4940
4941 /* If it could match, try it. */
4942 if (rst->nextb == NUL'\000' || *reginput == rst->nextb
4943 || *reginput == rst->nextb_ic) {
4944 reg_save(&rp->rs_un.regsave, &backpos);
4945 scan = regnext(rp->rs_scan);
4946 status = RA_CONT2;
4947 break;
4948 }
4949 }
4950 if (status != RA_CONT2) {
4951 /* Failed. */
4952 regstack_pop(&scan);
4953 regstack.ga_len -= sizeof(regstar_T);
4954 status = RA_NOMATCH5;
4955 }
4956 }
4957 break;
4958 }
4959
4960 /* If we want to continue the inner loop or didn't pop a state
4961 * continue matching loop */
4962 if (status == RA_CONT2 || rp == (regitem_T *)
4963 ((char *)regstack.ga_data + regstack.ga_len) - 1)
4964 break;
4965 }
4966
4967 /* May need to continue with the inner loop, starting at "scan". */
4968 if (status == RA_CONT2)
4969 continue;
4970
4971 /*
4972 * If the regstack is empty or something failed we are done.
4973 */
4974 if (GA_EMPTY(&regstack)((&regstack)->ga_len <= 0) || status == RA_FAIL1) {
4975 if (scan == NULL((void*)0)) {
4976 /*
4977 * We get here only if there's trouble -- normally "case END" is
4978 * the terminating point.
4979 */
4980 EMSG(_(e_re_corr))emsg((char_u *)(gettext((char *)(e_re_corr))));
4981#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
4982 printf("Premature EOL\n");
4983#endif
4984 }
4985 if (status == RA_FAIL1)
4986 got_int = TRUE1;
4987 return status == RA_MATCH4;
4988 }
4989
4990 } /* End of loop until the regstack is empty. */
4991
4992 /* NOTREACHED */
4993}
4994
4995/*
4996 * Push an item onto the regstack.
4997 * Returns pointer to new item. Returns NULL when out of memory.
4998 */
4999static regitem_T *regstack_push(regstate_T state, char_u *scan)
5000{
5001 regitem_T *rp;
5002
5003 if ((long)((unsigned)regstack.ga_len >> 10) >= p_mmp) {
5004 EMSG(_(e_maxmempat))emsg((char_u *)(gettext((char *)(e_maxmempat))));
5005 return NULL((void*)0);
5006 }
5007 ga_grow(&regstack, sizeof(regitem_T));
5008
5009 rp = (regitem_T *)((char *)regstack.ga_data + regstack.ga_len);
5010 rp->rs_state = state;
5011 rp->rs_scan = scan;
5012
5013 regstack.ga_len += sizeof(regitem_T);
5014 return rp;
5015}
5016
5017/*
5018 * Pop an item from the regstack.
5019 */
5020static void regstack_pop(char_u **scan)
5021{
5022 regitem_T *rp;
5023
5024 rp = (regitem_T *)((char *)regstack.ga_data + regstack.ga_len) - 1;
5025 *scan = rp->rs_scan;
5026
5027 regstack.ga_len -= sizeof(regitem_T);
5028}

5030/*
5031 * regrepeat - repeatedly match something simple, return how many.
5032 * Advances reginput (and reglnum) to just after the matched chars.
5033 */
5034static int
5035regrepeat (
5036 char_u *p,
5037 long maxcount /* maximum number of matches allowed */
5038)
5039{
5040 long count = 0;
5041 char_u *scan;
5042 char_u *opnd;
5043 int mask;
5044 int testval = 0;
5045
5046 scan = reginput; /* Make local copy of reginput for speed. */
5047 opnd = OPERAND(p)((p) + 3);
5048 switch (OP(p)((int)*(p))) {
5049 case ANY20:
5050 case ANY20 + ADD_NL30:
5051 while (count < maxcount) {
5052 /* Matching anything means we continue until end-of-line (or
5053 * end-of-file for ANY + ADD_NL), only limited by maxcount. */
5054 while (*scan != NUL'\000' && count < maxcount) {
5055 ++count;
5056 mb_ptr_adv(scan)scan += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(scan) : 1;
5057 }
5058 if (!REG_MULTI(reg_match == ((void*)0)) || !WITH_NL(OP(p))((((int)*(p))) >= 20 + 30 && (((int)*(p))) <= 48
+ 30) || reglnum > reg_maxline
5059 || reg_line_lbr || count == maxcount)
5060 break;
5061 ++count; /* count the line-break */
5062 reg_nextline();
5063 scan = reginput;
5064 if (got_int)
5065 break;
5066 }
5067 break;
5068
5069 case IDENT23:
5070 case IDENT23 + ADD_NL30:
5071 testval = TRUE1;
5072 /*FALLTHROUGH*/
5073 case SIDENT24:
5074 case SIDENT24 + ADD_NL30:
5075 while (count < maxcount) {
5076 if (vim_isIDc(PTR2CHAR(scan)(has_mbyte ? mb_ptr2char(scan) : (int)*(scan))) && (testval || !VIM_ISDIGIT(*scan)((unsigned)(*scan) - '0' < 10))) {
5077 mb_ptr_adv(scan)scan += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(scan) : 1;
5078 } else if (*scan == NUL'\000') {
5079 if (!REG_MULTI(reg_match == ((void*)0)) || !WITH_NL(OP(p))((((int)*(p))) >= 20 + 30 && (((int)*(p))) <= 48
+ 30) || reglnum > reg_maxline
5080 || reg_line_lbr)
5081 break;
5082 reg_nextline();
5083 scan = reginput;
5084 if (got_int)
5085 break;
5086 } else if (reg_line_lbr && *scan == '\n' && WITH_NL(OP(p))((((int)*(p))) >= 20 + 30 && (((int)*(p))) <= 48
+ 30))
5087 ++scan;
5088 else
5089 break;
5090 ++count;
5091 }
5092 break;
5093
5094 case KWORD25:
5095 case KWORD25 + ADD_NL30:
5096 testval = TRUE1;
5097 /*FALLTHROUGH*/
5098 case SKWORD26:
5099 case SKWORD26 + ADD_NL30:
5100 while (count < maxcount) {
5101 if (vim_iswordp_buf(scan, reg_buf)
5102 && (testval || !VIM_ISDIGIT(*scan)((unsigned)(*scan) - '0' < 10))) {
5103 mb_ptr_adv(scan)scan += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(scan) : 1;
5104 } else if (*scan == NUL'\000') {
5105 if (!REG_MULTI(reg_match == ((void*)0)) || !WITH_NL(OP(p))((((int)*(p))) >= 20 + 30 && (((int)*(p))) <= 48
+ 30) || reglnum > reg_maxline
5106 || reg_line_lbr)
5107 break;
5108 reg_nextline();
5109 scan = reginput;
5110 if (got_int)
5111 break;
5112 } else if (reg_line_lbr && *scan == '\n' && WITH_NL(OP(p))((((int)*(p))) >= 20 + 30 && (((int)*(p))) <= 48
+ 30))
5113 ++scan;
5114 else
5115 break;
5116 ++count;
5117 }
5118 break;
5119
5120 case FNAME27:
5121 case FNAME27 + ADD_NL30:
5122 testval = TRUE1;
5123 /*FALLTHROUGH*/
5124 case SFNAME28:
5125 case SFNAME28 + ADD_NL30:
5126 while (count < maxcount) {
5127 if (vim_isfilec(PTR2CHAR(scan)(has_mbyte ? mb_ptr2char(scan) : (int)*(scan))) && (testval || !VIM_ISDIGIT(*scan)((unsigned)(*scan) - '0' < 10))) {
5128 mb_ptr_adv(scan)scan += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(scan) : 1;
5129 } else if (*scan == NUL'\000') {
5130 if (!REG_MULTI(reg_match == ((void*)0)) || !WITH_NL(OP(p))((((int)*(p))) >= 20 + 30 && (((int)*(p))) <= 48
+ 30) || reglnum > reg_maxline
5131 || reg_line_lbr)
5132 break;
5133 reg_nextline();
5134 scan = reginput;
5135 if (got_int)
5136 break;
5137 } else if (reg_line_lbr && *scan == '\n' && WITH_NL(OP(p))((((int)*(p))) >= 20 + 30 && (((int)*(p))) <= 48
+ 30))
5138 ++scan;
5139 else
5140 break;
5141 ++count;
5142 }
5143 break;
5144
5145 case PRINT29:
5146 case PRINT29 + ADD_NL30:
5147 testval = TRUE1;
5148 /*FALLTHROUGH*/
5149 case SPRINT30:
5150 case SPRINT30 + ADD_NL30:
5151 while (count < maxcount) {
5152 if (*scan == NUL'\000') {
5153 if (!REG_MULTI(reg_match == ((void*)0)) || !WITH_NL(OP(p))((((int)*(p))) >= 20 + 30 && (((int)*(p))) <= 48
+ 30) || reglnum > reg_maxline
5154 || reg_line_lbr)
5155 break;
5156 reg_nextline();
5157 scan = reginput;
5158 if (got_int)
5159 break;
5160 } else if (vim_isprintc(PTR2CHAR(scan)(has_mbyte ? mb_ptr2char(scan) : (int)*(scan))) == 1
5161 && (testval || !VIM_ISDIGIT(*scan)((unsigned)(*scan) - '0' < 10))) {
5162 mb_ptr_adv(scan)scan += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(scan) : 1;
5163 } else if (reg_line_lbr && *scan == '\n' && WITH_NL(OP(p))((((int)*(p))) >= 20 + 30 && (((int)*(p))) <= 48
+ 30))
5164 ++scan;
5165 else
5166 break;
5167 ++count;
5168 }
5169 break;
5170
5171 case WHITE31:
5172 case WHITE31 + ADD_NL30:
5173 testval = mask = RI_WHITE0x100;
5174do_class:
5175 while (count < maxcount) {
5176 int l;
5177 if (*scan == NUL'\000') {
5178 if (!REG_MULTI(reg_match == ((void*)0)) || !WITH_NL(OP(p))((((int)*(p))) >= 20 + 30 && (((int)*(p))) <= 48
+ 30) || reglnum > reg_maxline
5179 || reg_line_lbr)
5180 break;
5181 reg_nextline();
5182 scan = reginput;
5183 if (got_int)
5184 break;
5185 } else if (has_mbyte && (l = (*mb_ptr2len)(scan)) > 1) {
5186 if (testval != 0)
5187 break;
5188 scan += l;
5189 } else if ((class_tab[*scan] & mask) == testval)
5190 ++scan;
5191 else if (reg_line_lbr && *scan == '\n' && WITH_NL(OP(p))((((int)*(p))) >= 20 + 30 && (((int)*(p))) <= 48
+ 30))
5192 ++scan;
5193 else
5194 break;
5195 ++count;
5196 }
5197 break;
5198
5199 case NWHITE32:
5200 case NWHITE32 + ADD_NL30:
5201 mask = RI_WHITE0x100;
5202 goto do_class;
5203 case DIGIT33:
5204 case DIGIT33 + ADD_NL30:
5205 testval = mask = RI_DIGIT0x01;
5206 goto do_class;
5207 case NDIGIT34:
5208 case NDIGIT34 + ADD_NL30:
5209 mask = RI_DIGIT0x01;
5210 goto do_class;
5211 case HEX35:
5212 case HEX35 + ADD_NL30:
5213 testval = mask = RI_HEX0x02;
5214 goto do_class;
5215 case NHEX36:
5216 case NHEX36 + ADD_NL30:
5217 mask = RI_HEX0x02;
5218 goto do_class;
5219 case OCTAL37:
5220 case OCTAL37 + ADD_NL30:
5221 testval = mask = RI_OCTAL0x04;
5222 goto do_class;
5223 case NOCTAL38:
5224 case NOCTAL38 + ADD_NL30:
5225 mask = RI_OCTAL0x04;
5226 goto do_class;
5227 case WORD39:
5228 case WORD39 + ADD_NL30:
5229 testval = mask = RI_WORD0x08;
5230 goto do_class;
5231 case NWORD40:
5232 case NWORD40 + ADD_NL30:
5233 mask = RI_WORD0x08;
5234 goto do_class;
5235 case HEAD41:
5236 case HEAD41 + ADD_NL30:
5237 testval = mask = RI_HEAD0x10;
5238 goto do_class;
5239 case NHEAD42:
5240 case NHEAD42 + ADD_NL30:
5241 mask = RI_HEAD0x10;
5242 goto do_class;
5243 case ALPHA43:
5244 case ALPHA43 + ADD_NL30:
5245 testval = mask = RI_ALPHA0x20;
5246 goto do_class;
5247 case NALPHA44:
5248 case NALPHA44 + ADD_NL30:
5249 mask = RI_ALPHA0x20;
5250 goto do_class;
5251 case LOWER45:
5252 case LOWER45 + ADD_NL30:
5253 testval = mask = RI_LOWER0x40;
5254 goto do_class;
5255 case NLOWER46:
5256 case NLOWER46 + ADD_NL30:
5257 mask = RI_LOWER0x40;
5258 goto do_class;
5259 case UPPER47:
5260 case UPPER47 + ADD_NL30:
5261 testval = mask = RI_UPPER0x80;
5262 goto do_class;
5263 case NUPPER48:
5264 case NUPPER48 + ADD_NL30:
5265 mask = RI_UPPER0x80;
5266 goto do_class;
5267
5268 case EXACTLY5:
5269 {
5270 int cu, cl;
5271
5272 /* This doesn't do a multi-byte character, because a MULTIBYTECODE
5273 * would have been used for it. It does handle single-byte
5274 * characters, such as latin1. */
5275 if (ireg_ic) {
5276 cu = vim_toupper(*opnd);
5277 cl = vim_tolower(*opnd);
5278 while (count < maxcount && (*scan == cu || *scan == cl)) {
5279 count++;
5280 scan++;
5281 }
5282 } else {
5283 cu = *opnd;
5284 while (count < maxcount && *scan == cu) {
5285 count++;
5286 scan++;
5287 }
5288 }
5289 break;
5290 }
5291
5292 case MULTIBYTECODE200:
5293 {
5294 int i, len, cf = 0;
5295
5296 /* Safety check (just in case 'encoding' was changed since
5297 * compiling the program). */
5298 if ((len = (*mb_ptr2len)(opnd)) > 1) {
5299 if (ireg_ic && enc_utf8)
5300 cf = utf_fold(utf_ptr2char(opnd));
5301 while (count < maxcount) {
5302 for (i = 0; i < len; ++i)
5303 if (opnd[i] != scan[i])
5304 break;
5305 if (i < len && (!ireg_ic || !enc_utf8
5306 || utf_fold(utf_ptr2char(scan)) != cf))
5307 break;
5308 scan += len;
5309 ++count;
5310 }
5311 }
5312 }
5313 break;
5314
5315 case ANYOF21:
5316 case ANYOF21 + ADD_NL30:
5317 testval = TRUE1;
5318 /*FALLTHROUGH*/
5319
5320 case ANYBUT22:
5321 case ANYBUT22 + ADD_NL30:
5322 while (count < maxcount) {
5323 int len;
5324 if (*scan == NUL'\000') {
5325 if (!REG_MULTI(reg_match == ((void*)0)) || !WITH_NL(OP(p))((((int)*(p))) >= 20 + 30 && (((int)*(p))) <= 48
+ 30) || reglnum > reg_maxline
5326 || reg_line_lbr)
5327 break;
5328 reg_nextline();
5329 scan = reginput;
5330 if (got_int)
5331 break;
5332 } else if (reg_line_lbr && *scan == '\n' && WITH_NL(OP(p))((((int)*(p))) >= 20 + 30 && (((int)*(p))) <= 48
+ 30))
5333 ++scan;
5334 else if (has_mbyte && (len = (*mb_ptr2len)(scan)) > 1) {
5335 if ((cstrchr(opnd, (*mb_ptr2char)(scan)) == NULL((void*)0)) == testval)
5336 break;
5337 scan += len;
5338 } else {
5339 if ((cstrchr(opnd, *scan) == NULL((void*)0)) == testval)
5340 break;
5341 ++scan;
5342 }
5343 ++count;
5344 }
5345 break;
5346
5347 case NEWL18:
5348 while (count < maxcount
5349 && ((*scan == NUL'\000' && reglnum <= reg_maxline && !reg_line_lbr
5350 && REG_MULTI(reg_match == ((void*)0))) || (*scan == '\n' && reg_line_lbr))) {
5351 count++;
5352 if (reg_line_lbr)
5353 ADVANCE_REGINPUT()reginput += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(reginput) : 1;
5354 else
5355 reg_nextline();
5356 scan = reginput;
5357 if (got_int)
5358 break;
5359 }
5360 break;
5361
5362 default: /* Oh dear. Called inappropriately. */
5363 EMSG(_(e_re_corr))emsg((char_u *)(gettext((char *)(e_re_corr))));
5364#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
5365 printf("Called regrepeat with op code %d\n", OP(p)((int)*(p)));
5366#endif
5367 break;
5368 }
5369
5370 reginput = scan;
5371
5372 return (int)count;
5373}
5374
5375/*
5376 * regnext - dig the "next" pointer out of a node
5377 * Returns NULL when calculating size, when there is no next item and when
5378 * there is an error.
5379 */
5380static char_u *regnext(char_u *p)
5381{
5382 int offset;
5383
5384 if (p == JUST_CALC_SIZE((char_u *) -1) || reg_toolong)
5385 return NULL((void*)0);
5386
5387 offset = NEXT(p)(((*((p) + 1) & 0377) << 8) + (*((p) + 2) & 0377
));
5388 if (offset == 0)
5389 return NULL((void*)0);
5390
5391 if (OP(p)((int)*(p)) == BACK4)
5392 return p - offset;
5393 else
5394 return p + offset;
5395}
5396
5397/*
5398 * Check the regexp program for its magic number.
5399 * Return TRUE if it's wrong.
5400 */
5401static int prog_magic_wrong(void)
5402{
5403 regprog_T *prog;
5404
5405 prog = REG_MULTI(reg_match == ((void*)0)) ? reg_mmatch->regprog : reg_match->regprog;
5406 if (prog->engine == &nfa_regengine)
5407 /* For NFA matcher we don't check the magic */
5408 return FALSE0;
5409
5410 if (UCHARAT(((bt_regprog_T *)prog)->program)((int)*(char_u *)(((bt_regprog_T *)prog)->program)) != REGMAGIC0234) {
5411 EMSG(_(e_re_corr))emsg((char_u *)(gettext((char *)(e_re_corr))));
5412 return TRUE1;
5413 }
5414 return FALSE0;
5415}
5416
5417/*
5418 * Cleanup the subexpressions, if this wasn't done yet.
5419 * This construction is used to clear the subexpressions only when they are
5420 * used (to increase speed).
5421 */
5422static void cleanup_subexpr(void)
5423{
5424 if (need_clear_subexpr) {
5425 if (REG_MULTI(reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
5426 /* Use 0xff to set lnum to -1 */
5427 memset(reg_startpos, 0xff, sizeof(lpos_T) * NSUBEXP10);
5428 memset(reg_endpos, 0xff, sizeof(lpos_T) * NSUBEXP10);
5429 } else {
5430 memset(reg_startp, 0, sizeof(char_u *) * NSUBEXP10);
5431 memset(reg_endp, 0, sizeof(char_u *) * NSUBEXP10);
5432 }
5433 need_clear_subexpr = FALSE0;
5434 }
5435}
5436
5437static void cleanup_zsubexpr(void)
5438{
5439 if (need_clear_zsubexpr) {
5440 if (REG_MULTI(reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
5441 /* Use 0xff to set lnum to -1 */
5442 memset(reg_startzpos, 0xff, sizeof(lpos_T) * NSUBEXP10);
5443 memset(reg_endzpos, 0xff, sizeof(lpos_T) * NSUBEXP10);
5444 } else {
5445 memset(reg_startzp, 0, sizeof(char_u *) * NSUBEXP10);
5446 memset(reg_endzp, 0, sizeof(char_u *) * NSUBEXP10);
5447 }
5448 need_clear_zsubexpr = FALSE0;
5449 }
5450}
5451
5452/*
5453 * Save the current subexpr to "bp", so that they can be restored
5454 * later by restore_subexpr().
5455 */
5456static void save_subexpr(regbehind_T *bp)
5457{
5458 int i;
5459
5460 /* When "need_clear_subexpr" is set we don't need to save the values, only
5461 * remember that this flag needs to be set again when restoring. */
5462 bp->save_need_clear_subexpr = need_clear_subexpr;
5463 if (!need_clear_subexpr) {
5464 for (i = 0; i < NSUBEXP10; ++i) {
5465 if (REG_MULTI(reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
5466 bp->save_start[i].se_u.pos = reg_startpos[i];
5467 bp->save_end[i].se_u.pos = reg_endpos[i];
5468 } else {
5469 bp->save_start[i].se_u.ptr = reg_startp[i];
5470 bp->save_end[i].se_u.ptr = reg_endp[i];
5471 }
5472 }
5473 }
5474}
5475
5476/*
5477 * Restore the subexpr from "bp".
5478 */
5479static void restore_subexpr(regbehind_T *bp)
5480{
5481 int i;
5482
5483 /* Only need to restore saved values when they are not to be cleared. */
5484 need_clear_subexpr = bp->save_need_clear_subexpr;
5485 if (!need_clear_subexpr) {
5486 for (i = 0; i < NSUBEXP10; ++i) {
5487 if (REG_MULTI(reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
5488 reg_startpos[i] = bp->save_start[i].se_u.pos;
5489 reg_endpos[i] = bp->save_end[i].se_u.pos;
5490 } else {
5491 reg_startp[i] = bp->save_start[i].se_u.ptr;
5492 reg_endp[i] = bp->save_end[i].se_u.ptr;
5493 }
5494 }
5495 }
5496}
5497
5498/*
5499 * Advance reglnum, regline and reginput to the next line.
5500 */
5501static void reg_nextline(void)
5502{
5503 regline = reg_getline(++reglnum);
5504 reginput = regline;
5505 fast_breakcheck();
5506}
5507
5508/*
5509 * Save the input line and position in a regsave_T.
5510 */
5511static void reg_save(regsave_T *save, garray_T *gap)
5512{
5513 if (REG_MULTI(reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
5514 save->rs_u.pos.col = (colnr_T)(reginput - regline);
5515 save->rs_u.pos.lnum = reglnum;
5516 } else
5517 save->rs_u.ptr = reginput;
5518 save->rs_len = gap->ga_len;
5519}
5520
5521/*
5522 * Restore the input line and position from a regsave_T.
5523 */
5524static void reg_restore(regsave_T *save, garray_T *gap)
5525{
5526 if (REG_MULTI(reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
5527 if (reglnum != save->rs_u.pos.lnum) {
5528 /* only call reg_getline() when the line number changed to save
5529 * a bit of time */
5530 reglnum = save->rs_u.pos.lnum;
5531 regline = reg_getline(reglnum);
5532 }
5533 reginput = regline + save->rs_u.pos.col;
5534 } else
5535 reginput = save->rs_u.ptr;
5536 gap->ga_len = save->rs_len;
5537}
5538
5539/*
5540 * Return TRUE if current position is equal to saved position.
5541 */
5542static int reg_save_equal(regsave_T *save)
5543{
5544 if (REG_MULTI(reg_match == ((void*)0)))
5545 return reglnum == save->rs_u.pos.lnum
5546 && reginput == regline + save->rs_u.pos.col;
5547 return reginput == save->rs_u.ptr;
5548}
5549
5550/*
5551 * Tentatively set the sub-expression start to the current position (after
5552 * calling regmatch() they will have changed). Need to save the existing
5553 * values for when there is no match.
5554 * Use se_save() to use pointer (save_se_multi()) or position (save_se_one()),
5555 * depending on REG_MULTI.
5556 */
5557static void save_se_multi(save_se_T *savep, lpos_T *posp)
5558{
5559 savep->se_u.pos = *posp;
5560 posp->lnum = reglnum;
5561 posp->col = (colnr_T)(reginput - regline);
5562}
5563
5564static void save_se_one(save_se_T *savep, char_u **pp)
5565{
5566 savep->se_u.ptr = *pp;
5567 *pp = reginput;
5568}
5569
5570/*
5571 * Compare a number with the operand of RE_LNUM, RE_COL or RE_VCOL.
5572 */
5573static int re_num_cmp(long_u val, char_u *scan)
5574{
5575 long_u n = OPERAND_MIN(scan)(((long)(scan)[3] << 24) + ((long)(scan)[4] << 16
) + ((long)(scan)[5] << 8) + (long)(scan)[6]);
5576
5577 if (OPERAND_CMP(scan)(scan)[7] == '>')
5578 return val > n;
5579 if (OPERAND_CMP(scan)(scan)[7] == '<')
5580 return val < n;
5581 return val == n;
5582}
5583
5584/*
5585 * Check whether a backreference matches.
5586 * Returns RA_FAIL, RA_NOMATCH or RA_MATCH.
5587 * If "bytelen" is not NULL, it is set to the byte length of the match in the
5588 * last line.
5589 */
5590static int match_with_backref(linenr_T start_lnum, colnr_T start_col, linenr_T end_lnum, colnr_T end_col, int *bytelen)
5591{
5592 linenr_T clnum = start_lnum;
5593 colnr_T ccol = start_col;
5594 int len;
5595 char_u *p;
5596
5597 if (bytelen != NULL((void*)0))
5598 *bytelen = 0;
5599 for (;; ) {
5600 /* Since getting one line may invalidate the other, need to make copy.
5601 * Slow! */
5602 if (regline != reg_tofree) {
5603 len = (int)STRLEN(regline)strlen((char *)(regline));
5604 if (reg_tofree == NULL((void*)0) || len >= (int)reg_tofreelen) {
5605 len += 50; /* get some extra */
5606 free(reg_tofree);
5607 reg_tofree = xmalloc(len);
5608 reg_tofreelen = len;
5609 }
5610 STRCPY(reg_tofree, regline)strcpy((char *)(reg_tofree), (char *)(regline));
5611 reginput = reg_tofree + (reginput - regline);
5612 regline = reg_tofree;
5613 }
5614
5615 /* Get the line to compare with. */
5616 p = reg_getline(clnum);
5617 if (clnum == end_lnum)
5618 len = end_col - ccol;
5619 else
5620 len = (int)STRLEN(p + ccol)strlen((char *)(p + ccol));
5621
5622 if (cstrncmp(p + ccol, reginput, &len) != 0)
5623 return RA_NOMATCH5; /* doesn't match */
5624 if (bytelen != NULL((void*)0))
5625 *bytelen += len;
5626 if (clnum == end_lnum)
5627 break; /* match and at end! */
5628 if (reglnum >= reg_maxline)
5629 return RA_NOMATCH5; /* text too short */
5630
5631 /* Advance to next line. */
5632 reg_nextline();
5633 if (bytelen != NULL((void*)0))
5634 *bytelen = 0;
5635 ++clnum;
5636 ccol = 0;
5637 if (got_int)
5638 return RA_FAIL1;
5639 }
5640
5641 /* found a match! Note that regline may now point to a copy of the line,
5642 * that should not matter. */
5643 return RA_MATCH4;
5644}
5645
5646#ifdef BT_REGEXP_DUMP
5647
5648/*
5649 * regdump - dump a regexp onto stdout in vaguely comprehensible form
5650 */
5651static void regdump(char_u *pattern, bt_regprog_T *r)
5652{
5653 char_u *s;
5654 int op = EXACTLY5; /* Arbitrary non-END op. */
5655 char_u *next;
5656 char_u *end = NULL((void*)0);
5657 FILE *f;
5658
5659#ifdef BT_REGEXP_LOG
5660 f = fopen("bt_regexp_log.log", "a");
5661#else
5662 f = stdoutstdout;
5663#endif
5664 if (f == NULL((void*)0))
5665 return;
5666 fprintf(f, "-------------------------------------\n\r\nregcomp(%s):\r\n",
5667 pattern);
5668
5669 s = r->program + 1;
5670 /*
5671 * Loop until we find the END that isn't before a referred next (an END
5672 * can also appear in a NOMATCH operand).
5673 */
5674 while (op != END0 || s <= end) {
5675 op = OP(s)((int)*(s));
5676 fprintf(f, "%2d%s", (int)(s - r->program), regprop(s)); /* Where, what. */
5677 next = regnext(s);
5678 if (next == NULL((void*)0)) /* Next ptr. */
5679 fprintf(f, "(0)");
5680 else
5681 fprintf(f, "(%d)", (int)((s - r->program) + (next - s)));
5682 if (end < next)
5683 end = next;
5684 if (op == BRACE_LIMITS17) {
5685 /* Two ints */
5686 fprintf(f, " minval %" PRId64"l" "d" ", maxval %" PRId64"l" "d",
5687 (int64_t)OPERAND_MIN(s)(((long)(s)[3] << 24) + ((long)(s)[4] << 16) + ((
long)(s)[5] << 8) + (long)(s)[6]), (int64_t)OPERAND_MAX(s)(((long)((s) + 4)[3] << 24) + ((long)((s) + 4)[4] <<
16) + ((long)((s) + 4)[5] << 8) + (long)((s) + 4)[6]));
5688 s += 8;
5689 } else if (op == BEHIND11 || op == NOBEHIND12) {
5690 /* one int */
5691 fprintf(f, " count %" PRId64"l" "d", (int64_t)OPERAND_MIN(s)(((long)(s)[3] << 24) + ((long)(s)[4] << 16) + ((
long)(s)[5] << 8) + (long)(s)[6]));
5692 s += 4;
5693 } else if (op == RE_LNUM204 || op == RE_COL205 || op == RE_VCOL206) {
5694 /* one int plus comperator */
5695 fprintf(f, " count %" PRId64"l" "d", (int64_t)OPERAND_MIN(s)(((long)(s)[3] << 24) + ((long)(s)[4] << 16) + ((
long)(s)[5] << 8) + (long)(s)[6]));
5696 s += 5;
5697 }
5698 s += 3;
5699 if (op == ANYOF21 || op == ANYOF21 + ADD_NL30
5700 || op == ANYBUT22 || op == ANYBUT22 + ADD_NL30
5701 || op == EXACTLY5) {
5702 /* Literal string, where present. */
5703 fprintf(f, "\nxxxxxxxxx\n");
5704 while (*s != NUL'\000')
5705 fprintf(f, "%c", *s++);
5706 fprintf(f, "\nxxxxxxxxx\n");
5707 s++;
5708 }
5709 fprintf(f, "\r\n");
5710 }
5711
5712 /* Header fields of interest. */
5713 if (r->regstart != NUL'\000')
5714 fprintf(f, "start `%s' 0x%x; ", r->regstart < 256
5715 ? (char *)transchar(r->regstart)
5716 : "multibyte", r->regstart);
5717 if (r->reganch)
5718 fprintf(f, "anchored; ");
5719 if (r->regmust != NULL((void*)0))
5720 fprintf(f, "must have \"%s\"", r->regmust);
5721 fprintf(f, "\r\n");
5722
5723#ifdef BT_REGEXP_LOG
5724 fclose(f);
5725#endif
5726}
5727#endif /* BT_REGEXP_DUMP */

6072 p = "BRACE_LIMITS";
6073 break;
6074 case BRACE_SIMPLE14:
6075 p = "BRACE_SIMPLE";
6076 break;
6077 case BRACE_COMPLEX140 + 0:
6078 case BRACE_COMPLEX140 + 1:
6079 case BRACE_COMPLEX140 + 2:
6080 case BRACE_COMPLEX140 + 3:
6081 case BRACE_COMPLEX140 + 4:
6082 case BRACE_COMPLEX140 + 5:
6083 case BRACE_COMPLEX140 + 6:
6084 case BRACE_COMPLEX140 + 7:
6085 case BRACE_COMPLEX140 + 8:
6086 case BRACE_COMPLEX140 + 9:
6087 sprintf(buf + STRLEN(buf)strlen((char *)(buf)), "BRACE_COMPLEX%d", OP(op)((int)*(op)) - BRACE_COMPLEX140);
6088 p = NULL((void*)0);
6089 break;
6090 case MULTIBYTECODE200:
6091 p = "MULTIBYTECODE";
6092 break;
6093 case NEWL18:
6094 p = "NEWL";
6095 break;
6096 default:
6097 sprintf(buf + STRLEN(buf)strlen((char *)(buf)), "corrupt %d", OP(op)((int)*(op)));
6098 p = NULL((void*)0);
6099 break;
6100 }
6101 if (p != NULL((void*)0))
6102 STRCAT(buf, p)strcat((char *)(buf), (char *)(p));
6103 return (char_u *)buf;
6104}
6105#endif /* REGEXP_DEBUG */

6161
6162static void mb_decompose(int c, int *c1, int *c2, int *c3)
6163{
6164 decomp_T d;
6165
6166 if (c >= 0xfb20 && c <= 0xfb4f) {
6167 d = decomp_table[c - 0xfb20];
6168 *c1 = d.a;
6169 *c2 = d.b;
6170 *c3 = d.c;
6171 } else {
6172 *c1 = c;
6173 *c2 = *c3 = 0;
6174 }
6175}
6176
6177/*
6178 * Compare two strings, ignore case if ireg_ic set.
6179 * Return 0 if strings match, non-zero otherwise.
6180 * Correct the length "*n" when composing characters are ignored.
6181 */
6182static int cstrncmp(char_u *s1, char_u *s2, int *n)
6183{
6184 int result;
6185
6186 if (!ireg_ic)
6187 result = STRNCMP(s1, s2, *n)strncmp((char *)(s1), (char *)(s2), (size_t)(*n));
6188 else
6189 result = MB_STRNICMP(s1, s2, *n)mb_strnicmp((char_u *)(s1), (char_u *)(s2), (int)(*n));
6190
6191 /* if it failed and it's utf8 and we want to combineignore: */
6192 if (result != 0 && enc_utf8 && ireg_icombine) {
6193 char_u *str1, *str2;
6194 int c1, c2, c11, c12;
6195 int junk;
6196
6197 /* we have to handle the strcmp ourselves, since it is necessary to
6198 * deal with the composing characters by ignoring them: */
6199 str1 = s1;
6200 str2 = s2;
6201 c1 = c2 = 0;
6202 while ((int)(str1 - s1) < *n) {
6203 c1 = mb_ptr2char_adv(&str1);
6204 c2 = mb_ptr2char_adv(&str2);
6205
6206 /* decompose the character if necessary, into 'base' characters
6207 * because I don't care about Arabic, I will hard-code the Hebrew
6208 * which I *do* care about! So sue me... */
6209 if (c1 != c2 && (!ireg_ic || utf_fold(c1) != utf_fold(c2))) {
6210 /* decomposition necessary? */
6211 mb_decompose(c1, &c11, &junk, &junk);
6212 mb_decompose(c2, &c12, &junk, &junk);
6213 c1 = c11;
6214 c2 = c12;
6215 if (c11 != c12 && (!ireg_ic || utf_fold(c11) != utf_fold(c12)))
6216 break;
6217 }
6218 }
6219 result = c2 - c1;
6220 if (result == 0)
6221 *n = (int)(str2 - s2);
6222 }
6223
6224 return result;
6225}
6226
6227/*
6228 * cstrchr: This function is used a lot for simple searches, keep it fast!
6229 */
6230static char_u *cstrchr(char_u *s, int c)
6231{
6232 char_u *p;
6233 int cc;
6234
6235 if (!ireg_ic
6236 || (!enc_utf8 && mb_char2len(c) > 1)
6237 )
6238 return vim_strchr(s, c);
6239
6240 /* tolower() and toupper() can be slow, comparing twice should be a lot
6241 * faster (esp. when using MS Visual C++!).
6242 * For UTF-8 need to use folded case. */
6243 if (enc_utf8 && c > 0x80)
6244 cc = utf_fold(c);
6245 else if (vim_isupper(c))
6246 cc = vim_tolower(c);
6247 else if (vim_islower(c))
6248 cc = vim_toupper(c);
6249 else
6250 return vim_strchr(s, c);
6251
6252 if (has_mbyte) {
6253 for (p = s; *p != NUL'\000'; p += (*mb_ptr2len)(p)) {
6254 if (enc_utf8 && c > 0x80) {
6255 if (utf_fold(utf_ptr2char(p)) == cc)
6256 return p;
6257 } else if (*p == c || *p == cc)
6258 return p;
6259 }
6260 } else
6261 /* Faster version for when there are no multi-byte characters. */
6262 for (p = s; *p != NUL'\000'; ++p)
6263 if (*p == c || *p == cc)
6264 return p;
6265
6266 return NULL((void*)0);
6267}

6270* regsub stuff *
6271***************************************************************/

6277static fptr_T do_upper(int *d, int c)
6278{
6279 *d = vim_toupper(c);
6280
6281 return (fptr_T)NULL((void*)0);
6282}

6284static fptr_T do_Upper(int *d, int c)
6285{
6286 *d = vim_toupper(c);
6287
6288 return (fptr_T)do_Upper;
6289}
