6291static fptr_T do_lower(int *d, int c)
6292{
6293 *d = vim_tolower(c);
6294
6295 return (fptr_T)NULL((void*)0);
6296}
6297
6298static fptr_T do_Lower(int *d, int c)
6299{
6300 *d = vim_tolower(c);
6301
6302 return (fptr_T)do_Lower;
6303}
6304
6305/*
6306 * regtilde(): Replace tildes in the pattern by the old pattern.
6307 *
6308 * Short explanation of the tilde: It stands for the previous replacement
6309 * pattern. If that previous pattern also contains a ~ we should go back a
6310 * step further... But we insert the previous pattern into the current one
6311 * and remember that.
6312 * This still does not handle the case where "magic" changes. So require the
6313 * user to keep his hands off of "magic".
6314 *
6315 * The tildes are parsed once before the first call to vim_regsub().
6316 */
6317char_u *regtilde(char_u *source, int magic)
6318{
6319 char_u *newsub = source;
6320 char_u *tmpsub;
6321 char_u *p;
6322 int len;
6323 int prevlen;
6324
6325 for (p = newsub; *p; ++p) {
6326 if ((*p == '~' && magic) || (*p == '\\' && *(p + 1) == '~' && !magic)) {
6327 if (reg_prev_sub != NULL((void*)0)) {
6328 /* length = len(newsub) - 1 + len(prev_sub) + 1 */
6329 prevlen = (int)STRLEN(reg_prev_sub)strlen((char *)(reg_prev_sub));
6330 tmpsub = xmalloc(STRLEN(newsub)strlen((char *)(newsub)) + prevlen);
6331 /* copy prefix */
6332 len = (int)(p - newsub); /* not including ~ */
6333 memmove(tmpsub, newsub, (size_t)len);
6334 /* interpret tilde */
6335 memmove(tmpsub + len, reg_prev_sub, (size_t)prevlen);
6336 /* copy postfix */
6337 if (!magic)
6338 ++p; /* back off \ */
6339 STRCPY(tmpsub + len + prevlen, p + 1)strcpy((char *)(tmpsub + len + prevlen), (char *)(p + 1));
6340
6341 if (newsub != source) /* already allocated newsub */
6342 free(newsub);
6343 newsub = tmpsub;
6344 p = newsub + len + prevlen;
6345 } else if (magic)
6346 STRMOVE(p, p + 1)memmove((p), (p + 1), strlen((char *)(p + 1)) + 1); /* remove '~' */
6347 else
6348 STRMOVE(p, p + 2)memmove((p), (p + 2), strlen((char *)(p + 2)) + 1); /* remove '\~' */
6349 --p;
6350 } else {
6351 if (*p == '\\' && p[1]) /* skip escaped characters */
6352 ++p;
6353 if (has_mbyte)
6354 p += (*mb_ptr2len)(p) - 1;
6355 }
6356 }
6357
6358 free(reg_prev_sub);
6359 if (newsub != source) /* newsub was allocated, just keep it */
6360 reg_prev_sub = newsub;
6361 else /* no ~ found, need to save newsub */
6362 reg_prev_sub = vim_strsave(newsub);
6363 return newsub;
6364}
6365
6366static int can_f_submatch = FALSE0; /* TRUE when submatch() can be used */
6367
6368/* These pointers are used instead of reg_match and reg_mmatch for
6369 * reg_submatch(). Needed for when the substitution string is an expression
6370 * that contains a call to substitute() and submatch(). */
6371static regmatch_T *submatch_match;
6372static regmmatch_T *submatch_mmatch;
6373static linenr_T submatch_firstlnum;
6374static linenr_T submatch_maxline;
6375static int submatch_line_lbr;
6376
6377/*
6378 * vim_regsub() - perform substitutions after a vim_regexec() or
6379 * vim_regexec_multi() match.
6380 *
6381 * If "copy" is TRUE really copy into "dest".
6382 * If "copy" is FALSE nothing is copied, this is just to find out the length
6383 * of the result.
6384 *
6385 * If "backslash" is TRUE, a backslash will be removed later, need to double
6386 * them to keep them, and insert a backslash before a CR to avoid it being
6387 * replaced with a line break later.
6388 *
6389 * Note: The matched text must not change between the call of
6390 * vim_regexec()/vim_regexec_multi() and vim_regsub()! It would make the back
6391 * references invalid!
6392 *
6393 * Returns the size of the replacement, including terminating NUL.
6394 */
6395int vim_regsub(regmatch_T *rmp, char_u *source, char_u *dest, int copy, int magic, int backslash)
6396{
6397 reg_match = rmp;
6398 reg_mmatch = NULL((void*)0);
6399 reg_maxline = 0;
6400 reg_buf = curbuf;
6401 reg_line_lbr = TRUE1;
6402 return vim_regsub_both(source, dest, copy, magic, backslash);
6403}
6404
6405int vim_regsub_multi(regmmatch_T *rmp, linenr_T lnum, char_u *source, char_u *dest, int copy, int magic, int backslash)
6406{
6407 reg_match = NULL((void*)0);
6408 reg_mmatch = rmp;
6409 reg_buf = curbuf; /* always works on the current buffer! */
6410 reg_firstlnum = lnum;
6411 reg_maxline = curbuf->b_ml.ml_line_count - lnum;
6412 reg_line_lbr = FALSE0;
6413 return vim_regsub_both(source, dest, copy, magic, backslash);
6414}
6415
6416static int vim_regsub_both(char_u *source, char_u *dest, int copy, int magic, int backslash)
6417{
6418 char_u *src;
6419 char_u *dst;
6420 char_u *s;
6421 int c;
6422 int cc;
6423 int no = -1;
6424 fptr_T func_all = (fptr_T)NULL((void*)0);
6425 fptr_T func_one = (fptr_T)NULL((void*)0);
6426 linenr_T clnum = 0; /* init for GCC */
6427 int len = 0; /* init for GCC */
6428 static char_u *eval_result = NULL((void*)0);
6429
6430 /* Be paranoid... */
6431 if (source == NULL((void*)0) || dest == NULL((void*)0)) {
6432 EMSG(_(e_null))emsg((char_u *)(gettext((char *)(e_null))));
6433 return 0;
6434 }
6435 if (prog_magic_wrong())
6436 return 0;
6437 src = source;
6438 dst = dest;
6439
6440 /*
6441 * When the substitute part starts with "\=" evaluate it as an expression.
6442 */
6443 if (source[0] == '\\' && source[1] == '='
6444 && !can_f_submatch /* can't do this recursively */
6445 ) {
6446 /* To make sure that the length doesn't change between checking the
6447 * length and copying the string, and to speed up things, the
6448 * resulting string is saved from the call with "copy" == FALSE to the
6449 * call with "copy" == TRUE. */
6450 if (copy) {
6451 if (eval_result != NULL((void*)0)) {
6452 STRCPY(dest, eval_result)strcpy((char *)(dest), (char *)(eval_result));
6453 dst += STRLEN(eval_result)strlen((char *)(eval_result));
6454 free(eval_result);
6455 eval_result = NULL((void*)0);
6456 }
6457 } else {
6458 win_T *save_reg_win;
6459 int save_ireg_ic;
6460
6461 free(eval_result);
6462
6463 /* The expression may contain substitute(), which calls us
6464 * recursively. Make sure submatch() gets the text from the first
6465 * level. Don't need to save "reg_buf", because
6466 * vim_regexec_multi() can't be called recursively. */
6467 submatch_match = reg_match;
6468 submatch_mmatch = reg_mmatch;
6469 submatch_firstlnum = reg_firstlnum;
6470 submatch_maxline = reg_maxline;
6471 submatch_line_lbr = reg_line_lbr;
6472 save_reg_win = reg_win;
6473 save_ireg_ic = ireg_ic;
6474 can_f_submatch = TRUE1;
6475
6476 eval_result = eval_to_string(source + 2, NULL((void*)0), TRUE1);
6477 if (eval_result != NULL((void*)0)) {
6478 int had_backslash = FALSE0;
6479
6480 for (s = eval_result; *s != NUL'\000'; mb_ptr_adv(s)s += has_mbyte ? (*mb_ptr2len)(s) : 1) {
6481 /* Change NL to CR, so that it becomes a line break,
6482 * unless called from vim_regexec_nl().
6483 * Skip over a backslashed character. */
6484 if (*s == NL'\012' && !submatch_line_lbr)
6485 *s = CAR'\015';
6486 else if (*s == '\\' && s[1] != NUL'\000') {
6487 ++s;
6488 /* Change NL to CR here too, so that this works:
6489 * :s/abc\\\ndef/\="aaa\\\nbbb"/ on text:
6490 * abc\
6491 * def
6492 * Not when called from vim_regexec_nl().
6493 */
6494 if (*s == NL'\012' && !submatch_line_lbr)
6495 *s = CAR'\015';
6496 had_backslash = TRUE1;
6497 }
6498 }
6499 if (had_backslash && backslash) {
6500 /* Backslashes will be consumed, need to double them. */
6501 s = vim_strsave_escaped(eval_result, (char_u *)"\\");
6502 free(eval_result);
6503 eval_result = s;
6504 }
6505
6506 dst += STRLEN(eval_result)strlen((char *)(eval_result));
6507 }
6508
6509 reg_match = submatch_match;
6510 reg_mmatch = submatch_mmatch;
6511 reg_firstlnum = submatch_firstlnum;
6512 reg_maxline = submatch_maxline;
6513 reg_line_lbr = submatch_line_lbr;
6514 reg_win = save_reg_win;
6515 ireg_ic = save_ireg_ic;
6516 can_f_submatch = FALSE0;
6517 }
6518 } else
6519 while ((c = *src++) != NUL'\000') {
6520 if (c == '&' && magic)
6521 no = 0;
6522 else if (c == '\\' && *src != NUL'\000') {
6523 if (*src == '&' && !magic) {
6524 ++src;
6525 no = 0;
6526 } else if ('0' <= *src && *src <= '9') {
6527 no = *src++ - '0';
6528 } else if (vim_strchr((char_u *)"uUlLeE", *src)) {
6529 switch (*src++) {
6530 case 'u': func_one = (fptr_T)do_upper;
6531 continue;
6532 case 'U': func_all = (fptr_T)do_Upper;
6533 continue;
6534 case 'l': func_one = (fptr_T)do_lower;
6535 continue;
6536 case 'L': func_all = (fptr_T)do_Lower;
6537 continue;
6538 case 'e':
6539 case 'E': func_one = func_all = (fptr_T)NULL((void*)0);
6540 continue;
6541 }
6542 }
6543 }
6544 if (no < 0) { /* Ordinary character. */
6545 if (c == K_SPECIAL(0x80) && src[0] != NUL'\000' && src[1] != NUL'\000') {
6546 /* Copy a special key as-is. */
6547 if (copy) {
6548 *dst++ = c;
6549 *dst++ = *src++;
6550 *dst++ = *src++;
6551 } else {
6552 dst += 3;
6553 src += 2;
6554 }
6555 continue;
6556 }
6557
6558 if (c == '\\' && *src != NUL'\000') {
6559 /* Check for abbreviations -- webb */
6560 switch (*src) {
6561 case 'r': c = CAR'\015'; ++src; break;
6562 case 'n': c = NL'\012'; ++src; break;
6563 case 't': c = TAB'\011'; ++src; break;
6564 /* Oh no! \e already has meaning in subst pat :-( */
6565 /* case 'e': c = ESC; ++src; break; */
6566 case 'b': c = Ctrl_H8; ++src; break;
6567
6568 /* If "backslash" is TRUE the backslash will be removed
6569 * later. Used to insert a literal CR. */
6570 default: if (backslash) {
6571 if (copy)
6572 *dst = '\\';
6573 ++dst;
6574 }
6575 c = *src++;
6576 }
6577 } else if (has_mbyte)
6578 c = mb_ptr2char(src - 1);
6579
6580 /* Write to buffer, if copy is set. */
6581 if (func_one != (fptr_T)NULL((void*)0))
6582 /* Turbo C complains without the typecast */
6583 func_one = (fptr_T)(func_one(&cc, c));
6584 else if (func_all != (fptr_T)NULL((void*)0))
6585 /* Turbo C complains without the typecast */
6586 func_all = (fptr_T)(func_all(&cc, c));
6587 else /* just copy */
6588 cc = c;
6589
6590 if (has_mbyte) {
6591 int totlen = mb_ptr2len(src - 1);
6592
6593 if (copy)
6594 mb_char2bytes(cc, dst);
6595 dst += mb_char2len(cc) - 1;
6596 if (enc_utf8) {
6597 int clen = utf_ptr2len(src - 1);
6598
6599 /* If the character length is shorter than "totlen", there
6600 * are composing characters; copy them as-is. */
6601 if (clen < totlen) {
6602 if (copy)
6603 memmove(dst + 1, src - 1 + clen,
6604 (size_t)(totlen - clen));
6605 dst += totlen - clen;
6606 }
6607 }
6608 src += totlen - 1;
6609 } else if (copy)
6610 *dst = cc;
6611 dst++;
6612 } else {
6613 if (REG_MULTI(reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
6614 clnum = reg_mmatch->startpos[no].lnum;
6615 if (clnum < 0 || reg_mmatch->endpos[no].lnum < 0)
6616 s = NULL((void*)0);
6617 else {
6618 s = reg_getline(clnum) + reg_mmatch->startpos[no].col;
6619 if (reg_mmatch->endpos[no].lnum == clnum)
6620 len = reg_mmatch->endpos[no].col
6621 - reg_mmatch->startpos[no].col;
6622 else
6623 len = (int)STRLEN(s)strlen((char *)(s));
6624 }
6625 } else {
6626 s = reg_match->startp[no];
6627 if (reg_match->endp[no] == NULL((void*)0))
6628 s = NULL((void*)0);
6629 else
6630 len = (int)(reg_match->endp[no] - s);
6631 }
6632 if (s != NULL((void*)0)) {
6633 for (;; ) {
6634 if (len == 0) {
6635 if (REG_MULTI(reg_match == ((void*)0))) {
6636 if (reg_mmatch->endpos[no].lnum == clnum)
6637 break;
6638 if (copy)
6639 *dst = CAR'\015';
6640 ++dst;
6641 s = reg_getline(++clnum);
6642 if (reg_mmatch->endpos[no].lnum == clnum)
6643 len = reg_mmatch->endpos[no].col;
6644 else
6645 len = (int)STRLEN(s)strlen((char *)(s));
6646 } else
6647 break;
6648 } else if (*s == NUL'\000') { /* we hit NUL. */
6649 if (copy)
6650 EMSG(_(e_re_damg))emsg((char_u *)(gettext((char *)(e_re_damg))));
6651 goto exit;
6652 } else {
6653 if (backslash && (*s == CAR'\015' || *s == '\\')) {
6654 /*
6655 * Insert a backslash in front of a CR, otherwise
6656 * it will be replaced by a line break.
6657 * Number of backslashes will be halved later,
6658 * double them here.
6659 */
6660 if (copy) {
6661 dst[0] = '\\';
6662 dst[1] = *s;
6663 }
6664 dst += 2;
6665 } else {
6666 if (has_mbyte)
6667 c = mb_ptr2char(s);
6668 else
6669 c = *s;
6670
6671 if (func_one != (fptr_T)NULL((void*)0))
6672 /* Turbo C complains without the typecast */
6673 func_one = (fptr_T)(func_one(&cc, c));
6674 else if (func_all != (fptr_T)NULL((void*)0))
6675 /* Turbo C complains without the typecast */
6676 func_all = (fptr_T)(func_all(&cc, c));
6677 else /* just copy */
6678 cc = c;
6679
6680 if (has_mbyte) {
6681 int l;
6682
6683 /* Copy composing characters separately, one
6684 * at a time. */
6685 if (enc_utf8)
6686 l = utf_ptr2len(s) - 1;
6687 else
6688 l = mb_ptr2len(s) - 1;
6689
6690 s += l;
6691 len -= l;
6692 if (copy)
6693 mb_char2bytes(cc, dst);
6694 dst += mb_char2len(cc) - 1;
6695 } else if (copy)
6696 *dst = cc;
6697 dst++;
6698 }
6699
6700 ++s;
6701 --len;
6702 }
6703 }
6704 }
6705 no = -1;
6706 }
6707 }
6708 if (copy)
6709 *dst = NUL'\000';
6710
6711exit:
6712 return (int)((dst - dest) + 1);
6713}
6714
6715
6716/*
6717 * Call reg_getline() with the line numbers from the submatch. If a
6718 * substitute() was used the reg_maxline and other values have been
6719 * overwritten.
6720 */
6721static char_u *reg_getline_submatch(linenr_T lnum)
6722{
6723 char_u *s;
6724 linenr_T save_first = reg_firstlnum;
6725 linenr_T save_max = reg_maxline;
6726
6727 reg_firstlnum = submatch_firstlnum;
6728 reg_maxline = submatch_maxline;
6729
6730 s = reg_getline(lnum);
6731
6732 reg_firstlnum = save_first;
6733 reg_maxline = save_max;
6734 return s;
6735}
6736
6737/*
6738 * Used for the submatch() function: get the string from the n'th submatch in
6739 * allocated memory.
6740 * Returns NULL when not in a ":s" command and for a non-existing submatch.
6741 */
6742char_u *reg_submatch(int no)
6743{
6744 char_u *retval = NULL((void*)0);
6745 char_u *s;
6746 int round;
6747 linenr_T lnum;
6748
6749 if (!can_f_submatch || no < 0)
6750 return NULL((void*)0);
6751
6752 if (submatch_match == NULL((void*)0)) {
6753 ssize_t len;
6754
6755 /*
6756 * First round: compute the length and allocate memory.
6757 * Second round: copy the text.
6758 */
6759 for (round = 1; round <= 2; ++round) {
6760 lnum = submatch_mmatch->startpos[no].lnum;
6761 if (lnum < 0 || submatch_mmatch->endpos[no].lnum < 0)
6762 return NULL((void*)0);
6763
6764 s = reg_getline_submatch(lnum) + submatch_mmatch->startpos[no].col;
6765 if (s == NULL((void*)0)) /* anti-crash check, cannot happen? */
6766 break;
6767 if (submatch_mmatch->endpos[no].lnum == lnum) {
6768 /* Within one line: take form start to end col. */
6769 len = submatch_mmatch->endpos[no].col
6770 - submatch_mmatch->startpos[no].col;
6771 if (round == 2)
6772 STRLCPY(retval, s, len + 1)xstrlcpy((char *)(retval), (char *)(s), (size_t)(len + 1));
6773 ++len;
6774 } else {
6775 /* Multiple lines: take start line from start col, middle
6776 * lines completely and end line up to end col. */
6777 len = STRLEN(s)strlen((char *)(s));
6778 if (round == 2) {
6779 STRCPY(retval, s)strcpy((char *)(retval), (char *)(s));
6780 retval[len] = '\n';
6781 }
6782 ++len;
6783 ++lnum;
6784 while (lnum < submatch_mmatch->endpos[no].lnum) {
6785 s = reg_getline_submatch(lnum++);
6786 if (round == 2)
6787 STRCPY(retval + len, s)strcpy((char *)(retval + len), (char *)(s));
6788 len += STRLEN(s)strlen((char *)(s));
6789 if (round == 2)
6790 retval[len] = '\n';
6791 ++len;
6792 }
6793 if (round == 2)
6794 STRNCPY(retval + len, reg_getline_submatch(lnum),strncpy((char *)(retval + len), (char *)(reg_getline_submatch
(lnum)), (size_t)(submatch_mmatch->endpos[no].col))
6795 submatch_mmatch->endpos[no].col)strncpy((char *)(retval + len), (char *)(reg_getline_submatch
(lnum)), (size_t)(submatch_mmatch->endpos[no].col));
6796 len += submatch_mmatch->endpos[no].col;
6797 if (round == 2)
6798 retval[len] = NUL'\000';
6799 ++len;
6800 }
6801
6802 if (retval == NULL((void*)0)) {
6803 retval = xmalloc(len);
6804 }
6805 }
6806 } else {
6807 s = submatch_match->startp[no];
6808 if (s == NULL((void*)0) || submatch_match->endp[no] == NULL((void*)0))
6809 retval = NULL((void*)0);
6810 else
6811 retval = vim_strnsave(s, (int)(submatch_match->endp[no] - s));
6812 }
6813
6814 return retval;
6815}
6816
6817// Used for the submatch() function with the optional non-zero argument: get
6818// the list of strings from the n'th submatch in allocated memory with NULs
6819// represented in NLs.
6820// Returns a list of allocated strings. Returns NULL when not in a ":s"
6821// command, for a non-existing submatch and for any error.
6822list_T *reg_submatch_list(int no)
6823{
6824 if (!can_f_submatch || no < 0) {
6825 return NULL((void*)0);
6826 }
6827
6828 linenr_T slnum;
6829 linenr_T elnum;
6830 list_T *list;
6831 char_u *s;
6832
6833 if (submatch_match == NULL((void*)0)) {
6834 slnum = submatch_mmatch->startpos[no].lnum;
6835 elnum = submatch_mmatch->endpos[no].lnum;
6836 if (slnum < 0 || elnum < 0) {
6837 return NULL((void*)0);
6838 }
6839
6840 colnr_T scol = submatch_mmatch->startpos[no].col;
6841 colnr_T ecol = submatch_mmatch->endpos[no].col;
6842
6843 list = list_alloc();
6844
6845 s = reg_getline_submatch(slnum) + scol;
6846 if (slnum == elnum) {
6847 list_append_string(list, s, ecol - scol);
6848 } else {
6849 list_append_string(list, s, -1);
6850 for (int i = 1; i < elnum - slnum; i++) {
6851 s = reg_getline_submatch(slnum + i);
6852 list_append_string(list, s, -1);
6853 }
6854 s = reg_getline_submatch(elnum);
6855 list_append_string(list, s, ecol);
6856 }
6857 } else {
6858 s = submatch_match->startp[no];
6859 if (s == NULL((void*)0) || submatch_match->endp[no] == NULL((void*)0)) {
6860 return NULL((void*)0);
6861 }
6862 list = list_alloc();
6863 list_append_string(list, s, (int)(submatch_match->endp[no] - s));
6864 }
6865
6866 return list;
6867}

6903/* Which regexp engine to use? Needed for vim_regcomp().
6904 * Must match with 'regexpengine'. */
6905static int regexp_engine = 0;
6906#define AUTOMATIC_ENGINE0 0
6907#define BACKTRACKING_ENGINE1 1
6908#define NFA_ENGINE2 2
6909#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
6910static char_u regname[][30] = {
6911 "AUTOMATIC Regexp Engine",
6912 "BACKTRACKING Regexp Engine",
6913 "NFA Regexp Engine"
6914};
6915#endif
6916
6917/*
6918 * Compile a regular expression into internal code.
6919 * Returns the program in allocated memory.
6920 * Use vim_regfree() to free the memory.
6921 * Returns NULL for an error.
6922 */
6923regprog_T *vim_regcomp(char_u *expr_arg, int re_flags)
6924{
6925 regprog_T *prog = NULL((void*)0);
6926 char_u *expr = expr_arg;
6927
6928 regexp_engine = p_re;
6929
6930 /* Check for prefix "\%#=", that sets the regexp engine */
6931 if (STRNCMP(expr, "\\%#=", 4)strncmp((char *)(expr), (char *)("\\%#="), (size_t)(4)) == 0) {
6932 int newengine = expr[4] - '0';
6933
6934 if (newengine == AUTOMATIC_ENGINE0
6935 || newengine == BACKTRACKING_ENGINE1
6936 || newengine == NFA_ENGINE2) {
6937 regexp_engine = expr[4] - '0';
6938 expr += 5;
6939#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
6940 smsg((char_u *)"New regexp mode selected (%d): %s",
6941 regexp_engine,
6942 regname[newengine]);
6943#endif
6944 } else {
6945 EMSG(_(emsg((char_u *)(gettext((char *)("E864: \\%#= can only be followed by 0, 1, or 2. The automatic engine will be used "
))))
6946 "E864: \\%#= can only be followed by 0, 1, or 2. The automatic engine will be used "))emsg((char_u *)(gettext((char *)("E864: \\%#= can only be followed by 0, 1, or 2. The automatic engine will be used "
))));
6947 regexp_engine = AUTOMATIC_ENGINE0;
6948 }
6949 }
6950#ifdef REGEXP_DEBUG
6951 bt_regengine.expr = expr;
6952 nfa_regengine.expr = expr;
6953#endif
6954
6955 /*
6956 * First try the NFA engine, unless backtracking was requested.
6957 */
6958 if (regexp_engine != BACKTRACKING_ENGINE1)
6959 prog = nfa_regengine.regcomp(expr, re_flags);
6960 else
6961 prog = bt_regengine.regcomp(expr, re_flags);
6962
6963 if (prog == NULL((void*)0)) { /* error compiling regexp with initial engine */
6964#ifdef BT_REGEXP_DEBUG_LOG
6965 if (regexp_engine != BACKTRACKING_ENGINE1) { /* debugging log for NFA */
6966 FILE *f;
6967 f = fopen(BT_REGEXP_DEBUG_LOG_NAME, "a");
6968 if (f) {
6969 fprintf(f, "Syntax error in \"%s\"\n", expr);
6970 fclose(f);
6971 } else
6972 EMSG2("(NFA) Could not open \"%s\" to write !!!",emsg2((char_u *)("(NFA) Could not open \"%s\" to write !!!"),
(char_u *)(BT_REGEXP_DEBUG_LOG_NAME))
6973 BT_REGEXP_DEBUG_LOG_NAME)emsg2((char_u *)("(NFA) Could not open \"%s\" to write !!!"),
(char_u *)(BT_REGEXP_DEBUG_LOG_NAME));
6974 }
6975#endif
6976 /*
6977 * If the NFA engine failed, the backtracking engine won't work either.
6978 *
6979 if (regexp_engine == AUTOMATIC_ENGINE)
6980 prog = bt_regengine.regcomp(expr, re_flags);
6981 */
6982 }
6983
6984 return prog;
6985}
6986
6987/*
6988 * Free a compiled regexp program, returned by vim_regcomp().
6989 */
6990void vim_regfree(regprog_T *prog)
6991{
6992 if (prog != NULL((void*)0))
6993 prog->engine->regfree(prog);
6994}

6996/*
6997 * Match a regexp against a string.
6998 * "rmp->regprog" is a compiled regexp as returned by vim_regcomp().
6999 * Uses curbuf for line count and 'iskeyword'.
7000 *
7001 * Return TRUE if there is a match, FALSE if not.
7002 */
7003int
7004vim_regexec (
7005 regmatch_T *rmp,
7006 char_u *line, /* string to match against */
7007 colnr_T col /* column to start looking for match */
7008)
7009{
7010 return rmp->regprog->engine->regexec_nl(rmp, line, col, false0);
7011}
7012
7013/*
7014 * Like vim_regexec(), but consider a "\n" in "line" to be a line break.
7015 */
7016int vim_regexec_nl(regmatch_T *rmp, char_u *line, colnr_T col)
7017{
7018 return rmp->regprog->engine->regexec_nl(rmp, line, col, true1);
7019}
7020
7021/*
7022 * Match a regexp against multiple lines.
7023 * "rmp->regprog" is a compiled regexp as returned by vim_regcomp().
7024 * Uses curbuf for line count and 'iskeyword'.
7025 *
7026 * Return zero if there is no match. Return number of lines contained in the
7027 * match otherwise.
7028 */
7029long vim_regexec_multi(
7030 regmmatch_T *rmp,
7031 win_T *win, /* window in which to search or NULL */
7032 buf_T *buf, /* buffer in which to search */
7033 linenr_T lnum, /* nr of line to start looking for match */
7034 colnr_T col, /* column to start looking for match */
7035 proftime_T *tm /* timeout limit or NULL */
7036)
7037{
7038 return rmp->regprog->engine->regexec_multi(rmp, win, buf, lnum, col, tm);
7039}
